INSERT INTO `diagnostics` VALUES (1,1,3,1,'primary','completed','2025-05-16 06:25:50','2025-06-19 23:36:12',100,'- **Critical Issues**  \n  • Licence non-compliance: key manufacturing and roofing licences lapse soon, risking operational shutdown and hefty fines  \n  • Profitability slide: last year’s net loss of $50–100K, heavy reliance on overdrafts, credit cards and owner injections for cash flow  \n  • Succession gap: plan exists on paper but hasn’t been implemented; business cannot run without the owner (70% reliance)  \n  • Customer concentration and churn risk: 35% of revenue from the largest customer, 95% chance of losing key accounts, weak CRM utilisation  \n  • HR and culture deficits: poor team cohesion, difficulty recruiting qualified staff, no regular performance reviews  \n\n- **High-Level Goals**  \n  • Achieve full licence compliance and establish a rolling renewal calendar  \n  • Restore profitability through cost realignment, tighter working-capital management and debt reduction  \n  • Activate and test the succession plan to reduce owner dependency and secure continuity  \n  • Fortify customer retention and diversify the client base via a structured CRM and targeted marketing  \n\n- **Key Takeaways**  \n  • Documented processes exist but require a formal review schedule to remain effective  \n  • Technology stack (ERP, CRM, Xero, Infusionsoft) is in place but under-leveraged; data-driven insights are largely unused  \n  • WIP is bloated (c. $856K) against modest forward orders; inventory rationalisation will unlock trapped capital  \n  • Marketing spend isn’t tracked for ROI; clarity on spend effectiveness is essential before scaling activities  \n  • Staff remain under-utilised (busy rating 70%) due to feast-and-famine work cycles  \n\n- **Top Opportunities**  \n  • Cultivate a performance-focused culture: introduce regular reviews, training and clear KPIs to boost morale and productivity  \n  • Optimise sales and marketing: define a repeatable sa