amp; Regulatory</td>\n      <td>5.0</td>\n      <td>Green</td>\n      <td>8</td>\n      <td>Tax compliance is robust; maintain documentation and lodgement schedules.</td>\n      <td>Verify BAS, IAS and income-tax lodgements have been lodged and paid</td>\n    </tr>\n  </table>\n\n  <!-- 2 Advisor Report -->\n  <h1>Advisor Report</h1>\n  <h2>1. Executive summary</h2>\n  <p>\n    Chris, your business demonstrates strong financial management, up-to-date tax compliance and well-established operational and HR frameworks. The main areas for improvement lie in consistent people processes, formal brand guidelines, thorough due diligence documentation and consolidation of legal agreements. Focusing first on People, Brand, Due Diligence Preparation and Legal &amp; Compliance will reduce perceived buyer risk, streamline operations and enhance overall sale readiness.\n  </p>\n\n  <h2>2. Module findings</h2>\n  <h3>M1 Financial Clarity &amp; Reporting</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Key financial reports reviewed only quarterly.</li>\n        <li>Meetings with accountant occur quarterly.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Bookkeeper in place ensures accurate record-keeping.</li>\n        <li>BAS and tax returns are current and up to date.</li>\n        <li>Business generated a profit last year.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M2 Legal, Compliance &amp; Property</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Contract and licence records are not consolidated centrally.</li>\n        <li>No formal legal compliance audit in place.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>All licences are up to date.</li>\n        <li>Service level agreements exist with key third parties.</li>\n        <li>No active legal actions pending.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M3 Owner Dependency &amp; Operations</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Business cannot operate without owner input; 70% reliance.</li>\n        <li>No formal board or governance structure.</li>\n        <li>Senior management strategy meetings occur only monthly.</li>\n        <li>Business processes last updated over two years ago.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>All key processes and procedures are documented.</li>\n        <li>Divisional and team meetings are in place.</li>\n        <li>Technology systems are integrated and supported.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M4 People</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Multiple key employees create potential single-point risks.</li>\n        <li>Position descriptions reviewed over two years ago.</li>\n        <li>Performance reviews conducted only every six months.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>HR policies and procedures are established.</li>\n        <li>Team cohesion and interdependence are strong.</li>\n        <li>Key HR metrics (absenteeism, leave) are tracked.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M5 Customer, Product &amp; Revenue Quality</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>No formal sales and marketing plan documented.</li>\n        <li>Marketing ROI and sales data are not tracked or reported.</li>\n        <li>Profit margins are unknown; only 10% of customers on contracts.</li>\n        <li>Top three customers account for 50% of revenue.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Sales and marketing strategy exists and is regularly reviewed.</li>\n        <li>CRM system is in place and used effectively.</li>\n        <li>Customer segmentation and sales process are clearly defined.</li>\n        <li>Product and pricing reviews occur on an annual basis.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M6 Brand, IP &amp; Intangibles</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>No formal brand style guide to ensure consistency.</li>\n        <li>Website updates occur only annually.</li>\n        <li>Certain brand assets lack unified presentation.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Website is live and regularly refreshed.</li>\n        <li>Physical premises require no immediate appeal upgrades.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M7 Tax, Compliance &amp; Regulatory</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>None identified.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Activity statements and tax returns are all up to date.</li>\n        <li>Robust compliance processes are in place.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Strategic business plan not reviewed for over two years.</li>\n        <li>No international trading plan in place.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Strategic plan exists and can be updated.</li>\n        <li>Some due diligence documentation is already prepared.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h2>3. Module scores &amp; RAG ranking</h2>\n  <table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n    <tr>\n      <th>Module</th>\n      <th>Score</th>\n      <th>RAG</th>\n      <th>Rank</th>\n    </tr>\n    <tr><td>M4 People</td><td>2.4</td><td>Amber</td><td>1</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>M6 Brand, IP &amp; Intangibles</td><td>2.5</td><td>Amber</td><td>2</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</td><td>2.7</td><td>Amber</td><td>3</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>M2 Legal, Compliance &amp; Property</td><td>3.0</td><td>Amber</td><td>4</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>M5 Customer, Product &amp; Revenue Quality</td><td>3.0</td><td>Amber</td><td>5</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>M1 Financial Clarity &amp; Reporting</td><td>3.8</td><td>Green</td><td>6</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>M3 Owner Dependency &amp; Operations</td><td>3.8</td><td>Green</td><td>7</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>M7 Tax, Compliance &amp; Regulatory</td><td>5.0</td><td>Green</td><td>8</td></tr>\n  </table>\n\n  <h2>4. Task list by module</h2>\n\n  <h3>M1 Financial Clarity &amp; Reporting</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Establish a monthly financial reporting calendar including profit &amp; loss, inventory and absenteeism metrics.</li>\n    <li>Schedule quarterly meetings with the accountant to review performance and forecasts.</li>\n    <li>Maintain up-to-date BAS and income-tax lodgement records.</li>\n    <li>Confirm BAS and income-tax lodgements are current.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M2 Legal, Compliance &amp; Property</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Conduct a legal compliance audit for all contracts and licences.</li>\n    <li>Consolidate supplier, customer and contractor agreements in a central repository.</li>\n    <li>Review property leases and arrangements for any upcoming renewals.</li>\n    <li>Gather and review supplier, customer and contractor contracts.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M3 Owner Dependency &amp; Operations</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Develop a succession and delegation plan for all owner responsibilities.</li>\n    <li>Document all key business processes and assign ownership for regular updates.</li>\n    <li>Schedule monthly senior management strategy meetings to review big-picture goals.</li>\n    <li>Document owners\' daily and periodic duties.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M4 People</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Define critical roles and responsibilities and identify single-point dependencies.</li>\n    <li>Implement a quarterly performance review framework for all staff and contractors.</li>\n    <li>Create an HR metrics dashboard to monitor absenteeism, turnover and leave balances.</li>\n    <li>Review and update position descriptions annually.</li>\n    <li>Compile full staff list with roles, status, start dates and key-employee flag.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M5 Customer, Product &amp; Revenue Quality</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Develop and document a formal sales and marketing plan aligned to strategic goals.</li>\n    <li>Implement marketing ROI tracking and reporting for all campaigns.</li>\n    <li>Establish procedures for regular product/service reviews and pricing updates.</li>\n    <li>Ensure customer service protocols are documented and responsibilities assigned.</li>\n    <li>Segment customer database into existing, lapsed and prospects.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M6 Brand, IP &amp; Intangibles</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Develop a comprehensive brand style guide covering logos, fonts and tone.</li>\n    <li>Schedule quarterly reviews of brand assets for consistency.</li>\n    <li>Plan a detailed website audit to ensure brand alignment.</li>\n    <li>Audit brand assets (logos, style guide, website) for consistency.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M7 Tax, Compliance &amp; Regulatory</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Maintain lodgement and payment schedules for BAS, IAS and income-tax obligations.</li>\n    <li>Conduct quarterly reviews of tax compliance documentation.</li>\n    <li>Update regulatory registers and filing schedules as regulations change.</li>\n    <li>Verify BAS, IAS and income-tax lodgements have been lodged and paid.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Assemble a central due diligence data room with corporate documents and reports.</li>\n    <li>Review and update the strategic business plan on an annual basis.</li>\n    <li>Ensure all contracts, licences and agreements are current and accessible.</li>\n    <li>Populate data room with five-year financials, contracts, leases and licences.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h2>5. Additional bespoke tasks</h2>\n  <p>No additional bespoke tasks identified at this stage.</p>\n\n</body>\n</html>','2025-06-17 23:17:30','2025-06-18 00:34:16'),(12,17,3,1,'primary','completed','2025-06-19 23:19:12','2025-07-07 01:20:52',100,'**Critical Issues**  \n- Licence compliance gaps: key manufacturing, roofing and safety licences overdue or at risk.  \n- Erodin