 of insights.\",\"quickWins\":\"Increase financial report review frequency from quarterly to monthly.\"},{\"module\":\"M7\",\"rag\":\"Green\",\"score\":\"5.0\",\"rank\":\"8\",\"whyPriority\":\"Tax and activity statements fully up to date, demonstrating strong compliance.\",\"quickWins\":\"Maintain current lodgement schedules and collate ATO records for buyer review.\"}],\"advisorReport\":{\"overallAssessment\":\"Greenside Outdoor Living demonstrates strong financial performance, robust tax compliance and solid operational processes. Top priorities are enhancing brand consistency, updating strategic planning, strengthening HR documentation, legal and property compliance, and refining product and marketing strategies to maximise valuation.\",\"quickWinsSummary\":\"Draft a brand style guide and refresh the website; update and review the strategic business plan; implement quarterly performance reviews; audit SLAs and property requirements.\",\"roadmapExplanation\":\"Modules are ranked by average gap scores. Amber areas need targeted improvements to reduce buyer concerns; green areas require maintenance. The sequence delivers quick impact and mitigates key risks ahead of sale.\",\"risksOfInaction\":\"Ignoring brand and strategic planning gaps could undermine buyer confidence and valuation. Unaddressed HR and legal deficiencies may prolong due diligence and expose the business to continuity risks.\",\"nextSteps\":\"Please review this report and schedule a follow-up meeting within the next two weeks to assign responsibilities, set timelines for quick wins and advance the sale-readiness roadmap.\"}}','<html>\n<head>\n  <title>Sale-Ready Roadmap and Advisor Report</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>Roadmap</h1>\n  <table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n    <tr>\n      <th>Module</th>\n      <th>Score</th>\n      <th>RAG</th>\n      <th>Rank</th>\n      <th>Why Priority</th>\n      <th>Quick Wins</th>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>M6 Brand, IP &amp; Intangibles</td>\n      <td>2.5</td>\n      <td>Amber</td>\n      <td>1</td>\n      <td>Brand assets inconsistent: no style guide and infrequent website reviews risk buyer perception.</td>\n      <td>Draft and implement a brand style guide and update the website to reflect current identity.</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</td>\n      <td>2.7</td>\n      <td>Amber</td>\n      <td>2</td>\n      <td>Strategic plan review over two years ago; no international trading plan limits growth potential.</td>\n      <td>Update the strategic business plan and create a simple international trading plan draft.</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>M4 People</td>\n      <td>2.8</td>\n      <td>Amber</td>\n      <td>3</td>\n      <td>HR documentation and performance reviews infrequent; recruitment and retention processes underdeveloped.</td>\n      <td>Review and update position descriptions and implement a quarterly performance review schedule.</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>M2 Legal, Compliance &amp; Property</td>\n      <td>3.0</td>\n      <td>Amber</td>\n      <td>4</td>\n      <td>Legal and property compliance gaps around SLAs and property upgrades need attention.</td>\n      <td>Audit and renew all third-party SLAs and schedule property condition assessments.</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>M5 Customer, Product &amp; Revenue Quality</td>\n      <td>3.0</td>\n      <td>Amber</td>\n      <td>5</td>\n      <td>Lack of margin benchmarking and no formal sales/marketing plan pose product strategy risks.</td>\n      <td>Benchmark product margins against industry standards and draft a basic sales and marketing plan.</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>M3 Owner Dependency &amp; Operations</td>\n      <td>3.4</td>\n      <td>Amber</td>\n      <td>6</td>\n      <td>High owner dependency (70%) and limited governance structures create continuity risk.</td>\n      <td>Develop succession and backup plans for key owner duties to reduce single-person risk.</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>M1 Financial Clarity &amp; Reporting</td>\n      <td>3.8</td>\n      <td>Green</td>\n      <td>7</td>\n      <td>Strong financial controls but quarterly reporting limits timeliness of insights.</td>\n      <td>Increase financial report review frequency from quarterly to monthly.</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>M7 Tax, Compliance &amp; Regulatory</td>\n      <td>5.0</td>\n      <td>Green</td>\n      <td>8</td>\n      <td>Tax and activity statements fully up to date, demonstrating strong compliance.</td>\n      <td>Maintain current lodgement schedules and collate ATO records for buyer review.</td>\n    </tr>\n  </table>\n\n  <h1>Advisor Report</h1>\n\n  <h2>1. Executive summary</h2>\n  <p>\n    Chris, Greenside Outdoor Living Pty Ltd is a 27-year-old outdoor furniture manufacturer generating AUD 5–10 million in turnover. Founders Alan and Kate Turner are preparing to retire. The business exhibits robust profitability, up-to-date licences and tax compliance, and solid operational processes. To maximise valuation and buyer confidence, priority actions include establishing consistent brand guidelines, updating the strategic plan, strengthening HR documentation and performance reviews, consolidating legal and property compliance, and formalising sales and marketing processes.\n  </p>\n\n  <h2>2. Module findings</h2>\n  <h3>M1 Financial Clarity &amp; Reporting</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Key financial reports (P&amp;L, balance sheet, cash flow forecast) reviewed only quarterly.</li>\n        <li>Meetings with the accountant occur quarterly, limiting timely insights.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Bookkeeper in place ensures accurate records.</li>\n        <li>Business generated a profit last year; BAS and tax returns are current.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M2 Legal, Compliance &amp; Property</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Service level and other third-party agreements not centrally consolidated.</li>\n        <li>No formal legal compliance audit or documented process.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>All licences are current and no legal actions are pending.</li>\n        <li>Property lease terms are well documented.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M3 Owner Dependency &amp; Operations</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Business relies on owners for 70% of operations with no succession plan.</li>\n        <li>No board or formal governance structure in place.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Divisional and team meetings occur regularly and processes are documented.</li>\n        <li>Technology systems are integrated and supported by IT providers.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M4 People</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Position descriptions were last reviewed over two years ago.</li>\n        <li>Performance reviews conducted only every six months.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>HR policies and procedures are established and HR metrics are tracked.</li>\n        <li>Team cohesion is strong and there are no under-performing staff.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M5 Customer, Product &amp; Revenue Quality</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>No formal sales and marketing plan; marketing ROI not tracked.</li>\n        <li>Profit margins are not benchmarked; top three customers account for 50% of revenue.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Sales strategy exists and customer segmentation is clearly defined.</li>\n        <li>CRM system in place and product reviews occur annually.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M6 Brand, IP &amp; Intangibles</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>No formal brand style guide; website updates occur only annually.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Website is live and refreshed within the last 12 months.</li>\n        <li>Physical premises require no immediate external upgrades.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M7 Tax, Compliance &amp; Regulatory</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>None identified.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Activity statements and tax returns are fully up to date.</li>\n        <li>Compliance processes are robust and can be readily audited.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Strategic business plan not reviewed for over two years.</li>\n        <li>No international trading plan in place.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Strategic plan exists and can be refreshed quickly.</li>\n        <li>Some due diligence documents (financials, licences, leases) are already prepared.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h2>3. Module scores &amp; RAG ranking</h2>\n  <table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n    <tr>\n      <th>Module</th>\n      <th>Score</th>\n      <th>RAG</th>\n      <th>Rank</th>\n    </tr>\n    <tr><td>M6 Brand, IP &amp; Intangibles</td><td>2.5</td><td>Amber</td><td>1</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</td><td>2.7</td><td>Amber</td><td>2</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>M4 People</td><td>2.8</td><td>Amber</td><td>3</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>M2 Legal, Compliance &amp; Property</td><td>3.0</td><td>Amber</td><td>4</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>M5 Customer, Product &amp; Revenue Quality</td><td>3.0</td><td>Amber</td><td>5</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>M3 Owner Dependency &amp; Operations</td><td>3.4</td><td>Amber</td><td>6</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>M1 Financial Clarity &amp; Reporting</td><td>3.8</td><td>Green</td><td>7</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>M7 Tax, Compliance &amp; Regulatory</td><td>5.0</td><td>Green</td><td>8</td></tr>\n  </table>\n\n  <h2>4. Task list by module</h2>\n\n  <h3>M1 Financial Clarity &amp; Reporting</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Establish a monthly reporting calendar for P&amp;L, balance sheet, cash flow and inventory metrics.</li>\n    <li>Increase the frequency of accountant meetings from quarterly to monthly.</li>\n    <li>Maintain and verify all BAS and income-tax lodgements are current.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M2 Legal, Compliance &amp; Property</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Conduct a legal compliance audit covering all licences and third-party agreements.</li>\n    <li>Consolidate supplier, customer and contractor contracts in a central repository.</li>\n    <li>Schedule a property condition assessment ahead of the next lease review.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M3 Owner Dependency &amp; Operations</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Develop a succession and delegation plan for critical owner responsibilities.</li>\n    <li>Document all key processes and assign owners for regular reviews.</li>\n    <li>Implement governance by forming a board or advisory committee.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M4 People</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Review and update all position descriptions at least annually.</li>\n    <li>Implement a quarterly performance review framework for staff and contractors.</li>\n    <li>Create an HR dashboard to monitor absenteeism, turnover and leave balances.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M5 Customer, Product &amp; Revenue Quality</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Draft and document a formal sales and marketing plan aligned to strategic objectives.</li>\n    <li>Implement ROI tracking for all marketing activities.</li>\n    <li>Benchmark product margins against industry standards and adjust pricing accordingly.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M6 Brand, IP &amp; Intangibles</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Develop and approve a comprehensive brand style guide covering logos, fonts and communications.</li>\n    