ce of business debt; accountant meetings only once per year.</li>\n      <li>Opportunities: Bookkeeper in place; all repayment obligations met; activity statements and tax returns are current.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M2 Legal, Compliance & Property</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Concerns: None identified.</li>\n      <li>Opportunities: All licences up to date; no legal actions; service-level agreements and property condition are well managed.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M3 Owner Dependency & Operations</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Concerns: Business cannot operate without owners; no board; senior management meetings held ad hoc; operational reports not reviewed; no succession plan; technology platforms do not sync.</li>\n      <li>Opportunities: Divisional structure exists; processes are documented and were reviewed in the past six months; effective technology support; internal cover for key roles.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M4 People</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Concerns: Position descriptions exist only for some team members; performance reviews conducted only annually; presence of under-performing staff; recruiting needs and staff retention risks in next six months.</li>\n      <li>Opportunities: HR policies and procedures are in place; team cohesion is high; HR metrics are measured; position descriptions were updated recently.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M5 Customer, Product & Revenue Quality</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Concerns: Product/service review overdue by over a year; need to adjust product mix; low supplier barriers; no exclusivity agreements; no CRM system; marketing ROI unknown.</li>\n      <li>Opportunities: Pricing was updated three months ago; customers understand offerings; sales and marketing plan exists, is implemented and identifies growth areas; data capture and usage are effective; marketing results rated 7/10.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M6 Brand, IP & Intangibles</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Concerns: No formal style guide; branding consistency rated 7/10.</li>\n      <li>Opportunities: Website exists and was updated within six months; premises require no upgrades; brand assets are identifiable.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M7 Tax, Compliance & Regulatory</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Concerns: None identified.</li>\n      <li>Opportunities: All activity statements and tax returns are up to date.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Concerns: No strategic business plan; no formal due diligence data-room structure.</li>\n      <li>Opportunities: Strong compliance record provides a sound base for documentation.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h2>3. Task list by module</h2>\n\n    <h3>M1 Financial Clarity & Reporting</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Request access to the accounting platform and export financial reports.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M2 Legal, Compliance & Property</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Collect all legal-structure documents (constitutions, trusts, shareholder agreements).</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M3 Owner Dependency & Operations</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Document owners’ daily and periodic duties.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M4 People</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Compile full staff list with roles, status, start dates and key-employee flag.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M5 Customer, Product & Revenue Quality</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Segment customer database into existing customers, lapsed customers and target prospects.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M6 Brand, IP & Intangibles</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Audit brand assets (logos, style guide, website) for consistency.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M7 Tax, Compliance & Regulatory</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Verify BAS, IAS and income-tax lodgements have been lodged and paid.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Create secure data-room folder structure (financial, legal, operations, HR, IP).</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h2>4. Additional bespoke tasks</h2>\n\n    <h3>M1 Financial Clarity & Reporting</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Establish a regular monthly financial reporting schedule for P&L, cash flow and balance-sheet reviews.</li>\n      <li>Develop and document a formal debt management plan.</li>\n      <li>Schedule quarterly strategy meetings with the accountant to review forecasts and budgets.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M2 Legal, Compliance & Property</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>No additional bespoke tasks identified at this time.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M3 Owner Dependency & Operations</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Implement a fixed calendar for divisional and company-wide management meetings.</li>\n      <li>Develop and formalise a succession plan for owners and key executives.</li>\n      <li>Install or enhance an integrated dashboard for operational KPIs and report reviews.</li>\n      <li>Evaluate and integrate systems to ensure seamless data flow between platforms.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M4 People</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Review and update position descriptions for all team members.</li>\n      <li>Implement quarterly 1:1 performance reviews and development plans.</li>\n      <li>Create a recruitment and retention strategy to address upcoming staffing needs.</li>\n      <li>Design and deliver performance improvement plans for under-performing staff.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M5 Customer, Product & Revenue Quality</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Conduct a full review of the product and service portfolio within three months.</li>\n      <li>Negotiate exclusivity or preferred-supplier agreements to strengthen margins.</li>\n      <li>Select and implement a CRM system to centralise customer data and automate follow-up.</li>\n      <li>Set up processes to calculate and report marketing ROI by channel and campaign.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M6 Brand, IP & Intangibles</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Develop and formalise a comprehensive brand and style guide.</li>\n      <li>Ensure branding consistency across all digital and print materials.</li>\n      <li>Review premises