r>\n          <td>M4 People</td>\n          <td>Green</td>\n          <td>3.5</td>\n          <td>2</td>\n          <td>Gaps in people processes and reviews</td>\n          <td>Review and update all position descriptions</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n          <td>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</td>\n          <td>Green</td>\n          <td>4.0</td>\n          <td>3</td>\n          <td>Strategic plan review timing inconsistent</td>\n          <td>Create secure data-room folder structure (financial, legal, operations, HR, IP)</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n          <td>M5 Customer, Product &amp; Revenue Quality</td>\n          <td>Green</td>\n          <td>4.1</td>\n          <td>4</td>\n          <td>Mixed product/service strategy needs review</td>\n          <td>Segment customer database into existing, lapsed and prospects</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n          <td>M3 Owner Dependency &amp; Operations</td>\n          <td>Green</td>\n          <td>4.2</td>\n          <td>5</td>\n          <td>High owner dependency and some process gaps</td>\n          <td>Document owners\' daily and periodic duties</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n          <td>M6 Brand, IP &amp; Intangibles</td>\n          <td>Green</td>\n          <td>4.2</td>\n          <td>6</td>\n          <td>Brand assets update overdue</td>\n          <td>Audit brand assets (logos, style guide, website) for consistency</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n          <td>M2 Legal, Compliance &amp; Property</td>\n          <td>Green</td>\n          <td>5.0</td>\n          <td>7</td>\n          <td>Legal and property compliance strong</td>\n          <td>Collect all legal-structure documents (constitutions, trusts, shareholder agreements)</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n          <td>M7 Tax, Compliance &amp; Regulatory</td>\n          <td>Green</td>\n          <td>5.0</td>\n          <td>8</td>\n          <td>Tax compliance current, low risk</td>\n          <td>Verify BAS, IAS and income-tax lodgements have been lodged and paid</td>\n        </tr>\n      </tbody>\n    </table>\n\n    <h1>Advisor Report for Shannon Semenikow</h1>\n\n    <h2>1. Executive Summary</h2>\n    <p>The client operates a 14-year-old migration and education business with AUD 1–5 million annual revenue. Financial performance is profitable but hampered by irregular reporting and limited bookkeeping support. Operations and customer-facing processes are mature, yet there is some owner dependency and gaps in IT support. People management is sound overall, though key employee risks and under-performing staff require attention. Brand, legal, tax and compliance are well managed. A focused programme of tasks across financial clarity, people, due diligence and customer processes will optimise sale readiness.</p>\n\n    <h2>2. Module Findings</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>M1 Financial Clarity &amp; Reporting</strong>\n        <ul>\n          <li>Reporting occurs monthly but lacks formal review meetings.</li>\n          <li>No in-house bookkeeper; reliance on quarterly accountant meetings.</li>\n          <li>Debt exists but is serviced; full visibility through scheduled reports is missing.</li>\n        </ul>\n      </li>\n      <li><strong>M2 Legal, Compliance &amp; Property</strong>\n        <ul>\n          <li>No current legal actions; property commitments are up to date.</li>\n          <li>Documentation centralisation could be improved.</li>\n        </ul>\n      </li>\n      <li><strong>M3 Owner Dependency &amp; Operations</strong>\n        <ul>\n          <li>Operational processes are documented and reviewed semi-annually.</li>\n          <li>Business can operate without owners’ input but not without guidance.</li>\n          <li>IT systems lack dedicated support; potential risk for continuity.</li>\n        </ul>\n      </li>\n      <li><strong>M4 People</strong>\n        <ul>\n          <li>Position descriptions exist but last reviewed 12 months ago.</li>\n          <li>Under-performing staff and risk of staff loss in next 6 months.</li>\n          <li>Annual performance reviews insufficient for ongoing engagement.</li>\n        </ul>\n      </li>\n      <li><strong>M5 Customer, Product &amp; Revenue Quality</strong>\n        <ul>\n          <li>Product/service mix suits current market; margins unknown and supplier access risk exists.</li>\n          <li>No formal sales and marketing plan; ROI measurement for marketing spend absent.</li>\n        </ul>\n      </li>\n      <li><strong>M6 Brand, IP &amp; Intangibles</strong>\n        <ul>\n          <li>Website and style guide updated within 12 months but brand assets require consistency audit.</li>\n        </ul>\n      </li>\n      <li><strong>M7 Tax, Compliance &amp; Regulatory</strong>\n        <ul>\n          <li>All Activity Statements and tax returns are current; compliance is low risk.</li>\n        </ul>\n      </li>\n      <li><strong>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</strong>\n        <ul>\n          <li>Strategic business plan exists but review cycle can be formalised.</li>\n          <li>No structured data-room for due diligence documents.</li>\n        </ul>\n      </li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h2>3. Task List by Module (Library Tasks)</h2>\n    <h3>M1 Financial Clarity & Reporting</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Implement a formal monthly financial reporting process with standardised templates.</li>\n      <li>Engage a qualified bookkeeper to support day-to-day transaction recording.</li>\n      <li>Establish a debt register and reconcile it during each reporting period.</li>\n      <li>Schedule monthly finance review meetings with owners and accountant.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>M2 Legal, Compliance & Property</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Maintain a central register of all legal documents and lease agreements.</li>\n      <li>Review compliance calendar quarterly to anticipate upcoming obligations.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>M3 Owner Dependency & Operations</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Develop and implement an operations succession plan for key roles.</li>\n      <li>Formalise a quarterly strategy meeting with senior management and owners.</li>\n      <li>Engage an IT support service provider and define SLAs for response and resolution.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>M4 People</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Design and launch a quarterly performance-review cycle for all staff.</li>\n      <li>Create a staff retention programme targeting key employees.</li>\n      <li>Update HR policies to include clear protocols for under-performance and exit.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>M5 Customer, Product & Revenue Quality</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Develop a comprehensive sales and marketing plan with measurable objectives.</li>\n      <li>Conduct a margin analysis by product/service line and benchmark against industry.</li>\n      <li>Implement ROI tracking for all marketing spend.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>M6 Brand, IP & Intangibles</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Conduct a full brand audit across all channels and materials.</li>\n      <li>Update the style guide and enforce consistency standards organisation-wide.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>M7 Tax, Compliance & Regulatory</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Maintain an up-to-date lodgement calendar for BAS, IAS and income tax.</li>\n      <li>Review tax provisions annually with the accountant to ensure adequacy.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Create a secure data-room with standardised folder structure for due diligence.</li>\n      <li>Compile a due-diligence checklist covering financial, legal, operational and HR documents.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h2>4. Additional Bespoke Tasks</h2>\n    <h3>M1 Financial Clarity & Reporting</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Request access to the cloud accounting platform for the advisory team.</li>\n      <li>Export the last 12 months of profit and loss and balance-sheet reports.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>M3 Owner Dependency & Operations</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Document each owner’s daily and periodic duties in standard operating procedures.</li>\n      <li>Identify and appoint a secondary IT contact to reduce single-point dependency.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>M4 People</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Review and update all position descriptions within the next 30 days.</li>\n      <li>Conduct interim performance reviews for under-performing staff.</li>\n      <li>Develop a contingency plan for at-risk employees likely to depart.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>M5 Customer, Product & Revenue Quality</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Segment the customer database into existing, lapsed and prospect categories.</li>\n      <li>Create and document a standardised customer-onboarding process.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>M6 Brand, IP & Intangibles</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Audit all logos, templates and marketing collateral for version control.</li>\n      <li>Plan a website content update cycle to occur every six months.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Create a secure data-room folder structure covering financial, legal, operations, HR and IP.</li>\n      <li>Upload the strategic business plan and last 12 months of board and executive minutes.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h2>5. Conclusion</h2>\n    <p>This programme of financial, operational, people and due-diligence tasks will significantly enhance the business’s sale readiness. We recommend initiating M1 and M4 tasks immediately, with phased roll-out of remaining modules over the next 90 days. A follow-up review should be scheduled in 60 days to track progress and adjust priorities.</p>\n  </body>\n</html>','2025-08-19 00:32:20','2025-09-02 00:06:32'),(19,23,3,17,'primary','completed','2025-08-19 23:09:55','2025-08-19 23:45:40',100,'**Critical Issues**  \n- Persistent net loss of $50–100K and declining profitability amid industry downturn.  \n- Heavy reliance on owner (70% dependency) with no effective succession plan in place.  \n- Inadequate licence compliance despite hefty fees a