er structure.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h4>31–60 days</h4>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Standardise report review cadence with monthly financial meetings.</li>\n      <li>Formalise and execute service level agreements with key suppliers.</li>\n      <li>Develop and document succession backups for critical roles.</li>\n      <li>Roll out a quarterly performance review process for all staff.</li>\n      <li>Design and implement an articulated sales process.</li>\n      <li>Publish and enforce a formal style guide across all channels.</li>\n      <li>Confirm payroll licences and renewals are current.</li>\n      <li>Begin populating the data-room with contracts and financial statements.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h4>61–90 days</h4>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Finalise normalised EBITDA and prepare an add-backs schedule.</li>\n      <li>Train management and staff on updated HR policies and performance frameworks.</li>\n      <li>Implement CRM data-tracking for customer interactions and marketing ROI.</li>\n      <li>Execute premises refresh plan (paint, signage and branding updates).</li>\n      <li>Compile a comprehensive compliance register for tax, licences and regulations.</li>\n      <li>Draft vendor due diligence questionnaires and complete initial responses.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>5. Next steps</h3>\n    <p>\n      Schedule workshops with key stakeholders to initiate enhancements in financial reporting, legal compliance, HR management and sales processes immediately.\n    </p>\n  </body>\n</html>','2025-08-20 09:58:28','2025-08-20 10:37:33'),(21,25,3,19,'primary','completed','2025-08-21 01:17:46','2025-08-21 02:30:30',100,'- **Critical Issues**  \n  • Unprofitable operations with last year’s net loss of £50–100K and declining financial performance since acquisition  \n  • Heavy reliance on the owner (70% dependency) and no effective succession plan, leaving the business vulnerable if Peter is unavailable  \n  • License compliance gaps (roofers licence and manufacturing licence neari