gal, operations, HR, IP)</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>M4 People</td>\n    <td>Amber</td>\n    <td>2.4</td>\n    <td>3</td>\n    <td>Inconsistent HR processes and underperforming staff require immediate fix.</td>\n    <td>Compile full staff list with roles, status, start dates and key-employee flag</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>M5 Customer, Product &amp; Revenue Quality</td>\n    <td>Amber</td>\n    <td>2.6</td>\n    <td>4</td>\n    <td>Customer and product mix need refinement to sustain growth and margins.</td>\n    <td>Segment customer database into existing, lapsed and prospects</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>M3 Owner Dependency &amp; Operations</td>\n    <td>Amber</td>\n    <td>2.7</td>\n    <td>5</td>\n    <td>High owner dependency and undocumented processes risk operational continuity.</td>\n    <td>Document owners’ daily and periodic duties</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>M6 Brand, IP &amp; Intangibles</td>\n    <td>Amber</td>\n    <td>3.4</td>\n    <td>6</td>\n    <td>Premises require update; brand consistency scoring 5/10 highlights gaps.</td>\n    <td>Audit brand assets (logos, style guide, website) for consistency</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>M2 Legal, Compliance &amp; Property</td>\n    <td>Green</td>\n    <td>4.0</td>\n    <td>7</td>\n    <td>Legal, compliance and property are well managed, reducing transaction risks.</td>\n    <td>Collect all legal-structure documents (constitutions, trusts, shareholder agreements)</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>M7 Tax, Compliance &amp; Regulatory</td>\n    <td>Green</td>\n    <td>5.0</td>\n    <td>8</td>\n    <td>Tax and compliance fully up to date, providing confidence to buyers.</td>\n    <td>Verify BAS, IAS and income-tax lodgements have been lodged and paid</td>\n  </tr>\n</table>\n\n<h1>Advisor Report</h1>\n\n<h2>1. Executive Summary</h2>\n<p>Stacey’s business demonstrates strong legal, compliance and tax foundations but requires significant enhancement in financial reporting, due diligence preparation and owner dependency. People management, operational processes and customer/product quality present further gaps. Brand and digital assets are moderate but can be optimised to support valuation. Addressing these areas systematically will increase buyer confidence and maximise transaction value.</p>\n\n<h2>2. Module Findings</h2>\n\n<h3>M1 Financial Clarity &amp; Reporting (Amber)</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Concern: Management accounts and historical financials are incomplete and not standardised.</li>\n  <li>Opportunity: Establish consistent monthly reporting to highlight trends and profitability.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>M8 Due Diligence Preparation (Amber)</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Concern: Data-room structure is ad hoc and key documents are not consolidated.</li>\n  <li>Opportunity: Implement a secure, organised virtual data room to expedite buyer review.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>M4 People (Amber)</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Concern: Lack of formal HR processes and underperforming staff impact operational efficiency.</li>\n  <li>Opportunity: Standardise performance management and identify key talent for retention.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>M5 Customer, Product &amp; Revenue Quality (Amber)</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Concern: Customer mix lacks segmentation; low-margin products dilute profitability.</li>\n  <li>Opportunity: Target high-value segments and optimise product portfolio for margin uplift.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>M3 Owner Dependency &amp; Operations (Amber)</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Concern: Critical processes rely on owner knowledge and are undocumented.</li>\n  <li>Opportunity: Document core procedures to enable delegation and demonstrate continuity.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>M6 Brand, IP &amp; Intangibles (Amber)</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Concern: Inconsistent brand usage across assets and outdated premises affect perception.</li>\n  <li>Opportunity: Reinforce brand guidelines and refresh collateral to enhance market appeal.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>M2 Legal, Compliance &amp; Property (Green)</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Concern: Minor updates required to 