or:#f0ad4e;color:#000\">Amber</td>\n      <td>2.3</td>\n      <td>5</td>\n      <td>HR policies missing and staff cohesion low</td>\n      <td>Implement performance reviews; update job descriptions</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>M6 Brand, IP &amp; Intangibles</td>\n      <td style=\"background-color:#f0ad4e;color:#000\">Amber</td>\n      <td>2.8</td>\n      <td>6</td>\n      <td>Inconsistent brand presence and outdated materials</td>\n      <td>Audit brand assets; update style guide</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>M7 Tax, Compliance &amp; Regulatory</td>\n      <td style=\"background-color:#f0ad4e;color:#000\">Amber</td>\n      <td>3.0</td>\n      <td>7</td>\n      <td>Activity statements behind but tax returns up to date</td>\n      <td>Lodge overdue activity statements immediately</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</td>\n      <td style=\"background-color:#5cb85c;color:#fff\">Green</td>\n      <td>4.0</td>\n      <td>8</td>\n      <td>Strategic plan is current and robust</td>\n      <td>Begin populating data room with key documents</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h1>Advisor Report for Spin Test</h1>\n\n<h2>1. Executive Summary</h2>\n<p>The diagnostic reveals critical shortfalls in legal compliance, owner dependency and financial reporting. Operational processes, HR policies and sales functions require immediate attention. Brand consistency and marketing infrastructure are underdeveloped, while due diligence preparation and strategic planning are comparatively strong. Addressing red-flag areas will significantly enhance sale readiness.</p>\n\n<h2>2. Module Findings</h2>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>M2 Legal, Compliance &amp; Property</strong>: Active legal actions, overdue property upgrades.</li>\n  <li><strong>M3 Owner Dependency &amp; Operations</strong>: Excessive reliance on owners, undocumented processes, no succession plan.</li>\n  <li><strong>M1 Financial Clarity &amp; Reporting</strong>: Infrequent reporting, no bookkeeper, cash-flow reliance on debt.</li>\n  <li><strong>M5 Customer, Product &amp; Revenue Quality</strong>: No CRM, unsegmented customers, supplier contracts absent, high customer concentration.</li>\n  <li><strong>M4 People</strong>: HR policies missing, position descriptions outdated, team cohesion low, risk of staff loss.</li>\n  <li><strong>M6 Brand, IP &amp; Intangibles</strong>: No website or style guide, branding inconsistencies.</li>\n  <li><strong>M7 Tax, Compliance &amp; Regulatory</strong>: Activity statements overdue; tax returns current.</li>\n  <li><strong>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</strong>: Strategic plan current; data-room needs populating.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>3. Task List by Module</h2>\n\n<h3>M2 Legal, Compliance &amp; Property</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Conduct a full legal risk assessment against current actions.</li>\n  <li>Ensure all property leases and title documents are up to date.</li>\n  <li>Review and resolve each active legal action with external counsel.</li>\n  <li>Schedule and complete required property upgrades within 12 months.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>M3 Owner Dependency &amp; Operations</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Document all core business processes and procedures in SOP format.</li>\n  <li>Develop and implement a succession and contingency plan for owner absence.</li>\n  <li>Assign deputies for critical owner roles and train them accordingly.</li>\n  <li>Establish regular internal management and team meetings with agendas.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>M1 Financial Clarity &amp; Reporting</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Engage a qualified bookkeeper to maintain up-to-date ledgers.</li>\n  <li>Increase financial report reviews to a monthly cadence.</li>\n  <li>Schedule quarterly meetings with your accountant to discuss P&amp;L and cash flow.</li>\n  <li>Consolidate all debts into a manageable repayment plan.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>M5 Customer, Product &amp; Revenue Quality</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Segment the customer database into active, lapsed and target prospects.</li>\n  <li>Review and optimise the product/service mix against market demand.</li>\n  <li>Implement a CRM system to track customer interactions and sales data.</li>\n  <li>Negotiate and formalise supplier contracts and exclusivity where possible.</li>\n  <li>Develop and document a formal sales and marketing process.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>M4 People</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Develop and update position descriptions for every role.</li>\n  <li>Create and implement HR policies and procedures manual.</li>\n  <li>Conduct structured 1:1 performance reviews quarterly.</li>\n  <li>Run team-building sessions to improve cohesion and retention.</li>\n  <li>Establish metrics for HR data (absenteeism, turnover, satisfaction).</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>M6 Brand, IP &amp; Intangibles</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Perform a full audit of all brand assets and marketing materials.</li>\n  <li>Create and enforce a consistent style guide covering logo, fonts and colours.</li>\n  <li>Design and launch a professional business website.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>M7 Tax, Compliance &amp; Regulatory</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Lodge all overdue activity statements immediately.</li>\n  <li>Set up a calendar reminder for ongoing statutory lodgements.</li>\n  <li>Review tax compliance processes to prevent future delays.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Organise a data-room structure with clear folders and naming conventions.</li>\n  <li>Populate the room with the strategic plan, financials and legal documents.</li>\n  <li>Review all documents for completeness and currency.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>4. Additional Bespoke Tasks</h2>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>M3</strong>: Design and implement a divisional structure chart.</li>\n  <li><strong>M4</strong>: Develop a retention plan for key employees at risk.</li>\n  <li><strong>M5</strong>: Create customer service procedures for complaints and late payments.</li>\n  <li><strong>M6</strong>: Refresh external premises appearance where required.</li>\n  <li><strong>M8</strong>: Conduct a dry run of due diligence requests to identify gaps.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>5. Longer-Term Roadmap (6–12 months)</h2>\n<ul>\n  <li>Standardise and automate sales and marketing strategies.</li>\n  <li>Implement an ERP system to integrate financial and operational data.</li>\n  <li>Formalise a board or advisory panel to oversee governance.</li>\n  <li>Roll out a comprehensive succession plan covering all critical roles.</li>\n  <li>Enhance customer service with a dedicated team and tracked KPIs.</li>\n</ul>\n</html>','2025-08-26 22:27:19','2025-08-26 22:48:06'),(23,26,17,21,'primary','completed','2025-08-26 22:56:57','2025-08-26 23:04:00',100,'**Critical Issues**  \n• Persistent losses and customer attrition – net loss of $100k–250k last year and “loss of customers” flagged as a key concern.  \n• Regulatory and legal exposure – currently facing legal actions with no formal regulatory-compliance framework in place.  \n• Single-point dependency on the owner – business reliant 90% on Stacey; no documented processes or divisional structure.  \n• Financial administration gaps – BAS statements are overdue, no bookkeeper engaged, critical working-capital metrics (WIP, debtors, creditors) unknown.  \n• Under-developed tech and systems – processes undocumented, no automation or e-commerce capability, minimal tech stack (just Gmail).  \n\n**High-Level Goals**  \n1. Return to profitability by recapturing lost customers and optimising cost structure.  \n2. Establish robust governance: settle legal actions, embed regulatory-compliance controls and engage dedicated financial expertise.  \n3. Build scalable systems: document core processes, adopt basic automation tools and digital reporting dashboards.  \n4. Reduce single-point risk: develop succession plan, delegate responsibilities, and formalise internal meetings and strategy reviews.  \n\n**Key Takeaways**  \n• Owner reliance is a vulnerability – invest in team training, clear job descriptions and hand-over protocols.  \n• Financial visib