ng, immediate BAS lodgements.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M2 Legal, Compliance & Property</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li><strong>Concerns:</strong> Ongoing legal action unmanaged, incomplete property documentation.</li>\n    <li><strong>Opportunities:</strong> Conduct full legal audit, centralise property leases and maintenance records.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M3 Owner Dependency & Operations</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li><strong>Concerns:</strong> 90% reliance on owners, no documented processes or succession plan, no management or team meetings, no operational reporting.</li>\n    <li><strong>Opportunities:</strong> Document key processes and SOPs, establish leadership structure, implement basic operational metrics.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M4 People</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li><strong>Concerns:</strong> Low team cohesion, no HR data tracking on absenteeism or performance beyond reviews.</li>\n    <li><strong>Opportunities:</strong> Introduce HR metrics, team-building initiatives, update and standardise position descriptions.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M5 Customer, Product & Revenue Quality</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li><strong>Concerns:</strong> No supplier contracts or exclusivity, no sales and marketing strategy or CRM, high customer concentration risk.</li>\n    <li><strong>Opportunities:</strong> Secure supplier agreements, develop marketing strategy, segment customers and implement CRM.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M6 Brand, IP & Intangibles</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li><strong>Concerns:</strong> No website or style guide, inconsistent branding across channels.</li>\n    <li><strong>Opportunities:</strong> Create a corporate style guide, launch a basic website, audit all branding touchpoints.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M7 Tax, Compliance & Regulatory</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li><strong>Concerns:</strong> Activity Statements overdue despite up-to-date tax returns.</li>\n    <li><strong>Opportunities:</strong> Lodge all outstanding statements and implement a compliance calendar.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li><strong>Concerns:</strong> No international trading plan within the strategic business plan.</li>\n    <li><strong>Opportunities:</strong> Extend strategy to include overseas markets and schedule regular plan reviews.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h2>3. Task List by Module</h2>\n\n  <h3>M1 Financial Clarity & Reporting</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Engage a qualified bookkeeper to oversee daily transactions.</li>\n    <li>Schedule monthly meetings with your accountant to review financial statements.</li>\n    <li>Implement a cash-flow forecasting process.</li>\n    <li>Lodge all outstanding Activity Statements immediately.</li>\n    <li>Explore refinance options to reduce high-cost debt reliance.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M2 Legal, Compliance & Property</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Conduct a legal audit to identify and document all current actions.</li>\n    <li>Review and centralise property lease agreements and maintenance schedules.</li>\n    <li>Engage external legal counsel to manage ongoing litigation.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M3 Owner Dependency & Operations</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Develop and document key business processes and standard operating procedures.</li>\n    <li>Establish a structured succession plan with interim leadership assignment.</li>\n    <li>Schedule regular internal management and team meetings.</li>\n    <li>Form a board or advisory committee and create a board charter.</li>\n    <li>Implement basic operational reporting on key metrics.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M4 People</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Review and update all position descriptions.</li>\n    <li>Introduce team-building workshops to improve cohesion.</li>\n    <li>Implement HR metrics tracking for absenteeism and performance.</li>\n    <li>Conduct a full team cohesion assessment.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M5 Customer, Product & Revenue Quality</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Draft and finalise supplier contracts and exclusivity agreements.</li>\n    <li>Develop a comprehensive sales and marketing strategy.</li>\n    <li>Implement a customer segmentation framework.</li>\n    <li>Deploy a Customer Relationship Management (CRM) system.</li>\n    <li>Analyse and rebalance customer concentration risk.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M6 Brand, IP & Intangibles</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Design and approve a corporate style guide.</li>\n    <li>Develop and launch a basic business website.</li>\n    <li>Audit all physical and digital branding touchpoints for consistency.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M7 Tax, Compliance & Regulatory</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Submit all overdue Activity Statements to the ATO.</li>\n    <li>Establish a compliance calendar for future reporting deadlines.</li>\n    <li>Conduct a full review of past tax compliance records.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Expand the strategic business plan to include an international trading strategy.</li>\n    <li>Review and update the strategic plan every six months.</li>\n    <li>Identify target international markets and conduct feasibility studies.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h2>4. Additional Bespoke Tasks</h2>\n\n  <h3>M1 Financial Clarity & Reporting</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Negotiate overdraft facility terms with your bank.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M2 Legal, Compliance & Property</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Implement a risk register for legal and compliance issues.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M3 Owner Dependency & Operations</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Create internal training materials to support documented processes.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M4 People</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Introduce performance incentives tied to operational metrics.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M5 Customer, Product & Revenue Quality</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Establish a dedicated customer service team and formal procedures.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M6 Brand, IP & Intangibles</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Conduct a detailed user-experience review of the new website post-launch.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h2>5. Conclusion & Next Steps</h2>\n  <p>Immediate focus should be on stabi