ob at Forsyths every two months to review variances and tax planning.  \n\n4. Control Your Cost Base  \n  a. Your top three expense lines are contractors, casual and permanent staff.  Run a weekly labour-utilisation report to see idle time and peak demand.  \n  b. Where possible, shift work from higher-cost contractors to in-house employees during off-peak periods, or introduce flexible rosters to smooth out peaks.  \n  c. Benchmark contractor rates every six months to ensure you’re competitive.  \n\n5. Normalize EBITDA for Sale Preparation  \n  a. Identify one-off costs/add-backs (e.g. licence renewals, directors’ non-essential draws, major repairs).  \n  b. Produce an adjusted EBITDA showing the “true” recurring earnings.  This will improve your valuation multiple when you exit.  \n\n6. Build a Simple KPI Dashboard  \n  a. Track monthly:  \n     – Gross margin % = (Revenue – COGS) ÷ Revenue × 100  \n     – EBITDA margin % = EBITDA ÷ Revenue × 100  \n     – Stock days = (Average stock ÷ COGS) × 365  \n     – Debtor days = (Average debtors ÷ Credit sales) × 365  \n     – Creditor days = (Average creditors ÷ Purchases) × 365  \n  b. Highlight any red flags (e.g. stock days > 120, debtor days > 60, or cash runway < 8 weeks).  \n\nNext step: Which of these initiatives would you like to prioritise first? For example, shall we begin by calculating your current CCC with your actual DSO, DIO and DPO figures?','{\"id\":\"chatcmpl-BesyU84fOqNEU4EaqkDQvHirwTz7W\",\"object\":\"chat.completion\",\"created\":1749084142,\"model\":\"o4-mini-2025-04-16\",\"choices\":[{\"index\":0,\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Here are several targeted financial\\u2010improvement initiatives for Manuco, based on your current diagnostics:\\n\\n1. Strengthen Cash-Flow Visibility  \\n  a. Introduce a rolling 13-week cash-flow forecast.  Reconcile actual receipts\\/payments weekly, then project the next 13 weeks.  \\n  b. Use this to signal upcoming license renewals (e.g. manufacturi