"audio_tokens\":0,\"accepted_prediction_tokens\":0,\"rejected_prediction_tokens\":0}}}','2025-06-17 01:06:49','2025-06-17 01:06:49'),(15,11,'user','What is PPSR and hw do I use it?',NULL,NULL,'2025-06-17 01:07:37','2025-06-17 01:07:37'),(16,11,'assistant','Module M2 Legal, Compliance & Property – Score: 1.0 (Red)  \nFlagged Gap: security interests in your plant & equipment may not be perfected via PPSR registration.\n\n1. What is the PPSR?  \n   – The Personal Property Securities Register is Australia’s national online register of security interests in personal property (i.e. all assets other than land).  \n   – When you take finance over plant, machinery, vehicles, stock or receivables, you “perfect” your security interest by lodging a financing statement on the PPSR. That gives you priority over other creditors.  \n\n2. Why use it?  \n   – To check if an asset is already encumbered (so you don’t unknowingly buy or sell subject to another party’s security interest).  \n   – To perfect your own finance arrangements and protect your lending or lease arrangements.  \n   – To discharge or amend registrations when debts are repaid or equipment is sold.  \n\n3. How to access and search  \n   a. Go to https://www.ppsr.gov.au and create a user account.  \n   b. Under “Search the Register” you can:  \n      • Search by serial number or VIN (for vehicles/plant).  \n      • Search by debtor name or ABN to see all registrations against your business.  \n   c. Download or print search results for your files.  \n\n4. How to register (perfect) a security interest  \n   a. Select “Register a Financing Statement.”  \n   b. Enter:  \n      • Grantor (your business/entity name & ABN)  \n      • Secured party (the financier’s details)  \n      • Collateral description (e.g. “Chattel – Manufacturing Press Model X serial no. 12345”).  \n      • Duration (up to 7 years; renew if needed).  \n   c. Pay the modest registration fee (approx. $6–$8).  \n   d. Retain the registration number and an electronic copy of the financing statement.  \n\n5. How to amend or discharge  \n   – Once a loan is repaid or an asset sold, lodge a Financing Change Statement (Discharge) to remove the security interest.  \n   – This updates the register and clears the title for future dealings.  \n\n6. Next Legal Steps for Manuco  \n   1. Search the PPSR by your entity names (SMH Pty Ltd & HMY Pty Ltd) and by serial numbers of Equipment 1 & Equipment 2.  \n   2. Identify any unperfected interests – finance agreements that aren’t registered or registrations you must renew.  \n   3. Lodge financing statements for each piece of encumbered equipment within 21 days of the security agreement date.  \n   4. Prepare a schedule of PPSR registrations showing:  \n      • Asset description  \n      • Registration number  \n      • Expiry/renewal date  \n   5. On repayment of any finance, immediately file a discharge.  \n\nProbing Questions  \n • Have you or your financiers already lodged notices on the PPSR?  \n • Can you supply serial numbers or identifying details of all financed plant and vehicles?  \n • Would you like a template financing statement and a step-by-step registration guide?  \n\nOnce we confirm your current registrations and gaps, I can draft the necessary financing statements and schedule reminders to keep your PPSR notices up to date.','{\"id\":\"chatcmpl-BjF5WToQ1Vy9b6vmMPxKp7H4ynPuc\",\"object\":\"chat.completion\",\"created\":1750122458,\"model\":\"o4-mini-2025-04-16\",\"choices\":[{\"index\":0,\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Module M2 Legal, Compliance & Property \\u2013 Score: 1.0 (Red)  \\nFlagged Gap: security interests in your plant & equipment may not be perfected via PPSR registration.\\n\\n1. What is the PPSR?  \\n   \\u2013 The Personal Property Securities Register is Australia\\u2019s national online register of security interests in personal property (i.e. all assets other than land).  \\n   \\u2013 When you take finance over plant, machinery, vehicles, stock or receivables, you \\u201cperfect\\u201d your security interest by lodging a financing statement on the PPSR. That gives you priority over other creditors.  \\n\\n2. Why use it?  \\n   \\u2013 To check if an asset is already encumbered (so you don\\u2019t unknowingly buy or sell subject to another party\\u2019s security interest).  \\n   \\u2013 To perfect your own finance arrangements and protect your lending or lease arrangements.  \\n   \\u2013 To discharge or amend registrations when debts are repaid or equipment is sold.  \\n\\n3. How to access and search  \\n   a. Go to https:\\/\\/www.ppsr.gov.au and create a user account.  \\n   b. Under \\u201cSearch the Register\\u201d you can:  \\n      \\u2022 Search by serial number or VIN (for vehicles\\/plant).  \\n      \\u2022 Search by debtor name or ABN to see all registrations against your business.  \\n   c. Download or print search results for your files.  \\n\\n4. How to register (perfect) a security interest  \\n   a. Select \\u201cRegister a Financing Statement.\\u201d  \\n   b. Enter:  \\n      \\u2022 Grantor (your business\\/entity name & ABN)  \\n      \\u2022 Secured party (the financier\\u2019s details)  \\n      \\u2022 Collateral description (e.g. \\u201cChattel \\u2013 Manufacturing Press Model X serial no. 12345\\u201d).  \\n      \\u2022 Duration (up to 7 years; renew if needed).  \\n   c. Pay the modest registration fee (approx. $6\\u2013$8).  \\n   d. Retain the registration number and an electronic copy of the financing statement.  \\n\\n5. How to amend or discharge  \\n   \\u2013 Once a loan is repaid or an asset sold, lodge a Financing Change Statement (Discharge) to remove the security interest.  \\n   \\u2013 This updates the register and clears the title for future dealings.  \\n\\n6. Next Legal Steps for Manuco  \\n   1. Search the PPSR by your entity names (SMH Pty Ltd & HMY Pty Ltd) and by serial numbers of Equipment 1 & Equipment 2.  \\n   2. Identify any unperfected interests \\u2013 finance agreements that aren\\u2019t registered or registrations you must renew.  \\n   3. Lodge financing statements for each piece of encumbered equipment within 21 days of the security agreement date.  \\n   4. Prepare a schedule of PPSR registrations showing:  \\n      \\u2022 Asset description  \\n      \\u2022 Registration number  \\n      \\u2022 Expiry\\/renewal date  \\n   5. On repayment of any finance, immediately file a discharge.  \\n\\nProbing Questions  \\n \\u2022 Have you or your financiers already lodged notices on the PPSR?  \\n \\u2022 Can you supply serial numbers or identifying details of all financed plant and vehicles?  \\n \\u2022 Would you like a template financing statement and a step-by-step registration guide?  \\n\\nOnce we confirm your current registrations and gaps, I can draft the necessary financing statements and schedule reminders to keep your PPSR notices up to date.\",\"refusal\":null,\"annotations\":[]},\"finish_reason\":\"stop\"}],\"usage\":{\"prompt_tokens\":10777,\"completion_tokens\":1296,\"total_tokens\":12073,\"prompt_tokens_details\":{\"cached_tokens\":0,\"audio_tokens\":0},\"completion_tokens_details\":{\"reasoning_tokens\":576,\"audio_tokens\":0,\"accepted_prediction_tokens\":0,\"rejected_prediction_tokens\":0}},\"service_tier\":\"default\",\"system_fingerprint\":null}','{\"model\":\"o4-mini-2025-04-16\",\"usage\":{\"prompt_tokens\":10777,\"completion_tokens\":1296,\"total_tokens\":12073,\"prompt_tokens_details\":{\"cached_tokens\":0,\"audio_tokens\":0},\"completion_tokens_details\":{\"reasoning_tokens\":576,\"audio_tokens\":0,\"accepted_prediction_tokens\":0,\"rejected_prediction_tokens\":0}}}','2025-06-17 01:07:57','2025-06-17 01:07:57'),(17,16,'assistant','Hi Andrew, thanks for reviewing your Sale-Ready Roadmap and Advisor Report. Your top priority is Module 2: Legal, Compliance & Property (currently at an Amber RAG). To get the sale-ready process moving:\n\n1. We need to verify and update yo