ades.\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <strong>M3 Owner Dependency &amp; Operations</strong><br/>\n        Concerns: High owner reliance (70%), inability to operate without input, ad hoc senior management meetings, succession plan not implemented or effective, operational reports not reviewed. Opportunities: Clear governance via board and divisional structure, documented processes, available IT support, capable backup personnel.\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <strong>M4 People</strong><br/>\n        Concerns: Position descriptions incomplete, no performance review culture, risk of staff departure, under-performing staff, recruitment and induction weaknesses, poor team cohesion. Opportunities: HR policies in place, HR data tracked.\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <strong>M5 Customer, Product &amp; Revenue Quality</strong><br/>\n        Concerns: Product and service review overdue, low margins, product relevancy threatened in two years, missing sales process and plan, limited CRM use and data capture, low contract penetration, untrained customer service. Opportunities: Custom solutions are well regarded, prices recently updated, right product-market fit and strategic marketing framework exist.\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <strong>M6 Brand, IP &amp; Intangibles</strong><br/>\n        Concerns: No style guide, inconsistent branding, uncertain website currency, premises need external refresh. Opportunities: Established website and IP framework.\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <strong>M7 Tax, Compliance &amp; Regulatory</strong><br/>\n        Concerns: None. Opportunities: All lodgements and statements are current.\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <strong>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</strong><br/>\n        Concerns: No strategic business plan in place. Opportunities: International trading plan established.\n      </li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h2>3. Task List by Module</h2>\n    <h3>M1 Financial Clarity &amp; Reporting</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Request access to accounting platform and export historical financial reports.</li>\n      <li>Increase financial review frequency to monthly profit and loss analysis.</li>\n      <li>Schedule quarterly meetings with the accountant to discuss variances and forecasts.</li>\n      <li>Develop a rolling cashflow forecast to reduce reliance on overdraft facilities.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M2 Legal, Compliance &amp; Property</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Collect all legal-structure documents (constitutions, trusts, shareholder agreements).</li>\n      <li>Renew all business licences and maintain an expiry schedule.</li>\n      <li>Draft and execute service-level agreements with all key third-party suppliers.</li>\n      <li>Conduct a contract audit to identify any undocumented liabilities.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M3 Owner Dependency &amp; Operations</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Document owners’ daily and periodic duties in an operations manual.</li>\n      <li>Establish a governance framework with defined decision-making protocols.</li>\n      <li>Schedule regular monthly senior management meetings with formal agendas.</li>\n      <li>Implement a reporting cadence for key operational metrics and distribute to stakeholders.</li>\n      <li>Develop a plan to reduce owner reliance by delegating responsibilities.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M4 People</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Compile a comprehensive staff roster with roles, statuses, start dates and key-employee flags.</li>\n      <li>Review and update all position descriptions to reflect current requirements.</li>\n      <li>Implement a quarterly one-to-one performance review process.</li>\n      <li>Design a staff retention and succession plan for key roles at risk.</li>\n      <li>Provide training on recruitment, induction and exit procedures to HR staff.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M5 Customer, Product &amp; Revenue Quality</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Segment the customer database into existing, lapsed and prospect groups.</li>\n      <li>Conduct a full product and service portfolio review to identify gaps.</li>\n      <li>Develop and document a formal sales process and sales plan.</li>\n      <li>Integrate CRM usage into daily operations and train staff to improve CRM adoption.</li>\n      <li>Set up tracking for marketing spend ROI and customer lifetime value metrics.</li>\n      <li>Create or renew service contracts with top clients to increase revenue stability.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M6 Brand, IP &amp; Intangibles</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Audit all brand assets (logos, style guide, website) for consistency.</li>\n      <li>Develop and publish a comprehensive brand style guide.</li>\n      <li>Schedule a website content refresh and design facelift.</li>\n      <li>Refresh external premises (paint, signage) to align with brand guidelines.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M7 Tax, Compliance &amp; Regulatory</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Verify BAS, IAS and income-tax lodgements have been lodged and paid.</li>\n      <li>Institute an ongoing tax-compliance calendar with reminders for all lodgements.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Create a secure data-room folder structure covering financial, legal, operations, HR and IP documentation.</li>\n      <li>Develop a strategic business plan to articulate future vision and objectives.</li>\n      <li>Review and update the international trading plan to align with strategic objectives.</li>\n      <li>Compile due diligence documentation checklist and assign owners for each item.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h2>4. Additional Bespoke Tasks</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <li>M1: Reconcile past losses with corrective action plans for cost control and revenue enhancement.</li>\n      <li>M3: Formalise backup procedures for all critical owner functions within the systems environment.</li>\n      <li>M4: Organise team-building workshops to improve cohesion and collaboration.</li>\n      <li>M5: Train customer service personnel on complaint resolution and upsell techniques.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h2>5. Next Steps</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Implement quick-win tasks immediately to build momentum.</li>\n      <li>Assign clear ownership and deadlines for all tasks in each module.</li>\n      <li>Monitor progress through a weekly dashboard and adjust priorities as needed.</li>\n      <li>Engage specialist advisers (legal, tax, HR) to support complex tasks.</li>\n      <li>Review overall readiness monthly and prepare investor-grade documentation for sale.</li>\n    </ul>\n  </body>\n</html>','red','diagnostic','2025-07-07 02:20:51','2025-07-07 02:20:51'),(24,12,NULL,'Diagnostic Advice',1,0,'<html>\n<head>\n  <title>Sale-Ready Roadmap and Advisor Report</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>Roadmap</h1>\n  <table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n    <tr>\n      <th>Module</th>\n      <th>Score</th>\n      <th>RAG</th>\n      <th>Rank</th>\n      <th>Why Priority</th>\n      <th>Quick Wins</th>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>M6 Brand, IP &amp; Intangibles</td>\n      <td>2.5</td>\n      <td>Amber</td>\n      <td>1</td>\n      <td>Brand assets inconsistent: no style guide and infrequent website reviews risk buyer perception.</td>\n      <td>Draft and implement a brand style guide and update the website to reflect current identity.</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</td>\n      <td>2.7</td>\n      <td>Amber</td>\n      <td>2</td>\n      <td>Strategic plan review over two years ago; no international trading plan limits growth potential.</td>\n      <td>Update the strategic business plan and create a simple international trading plan draft.</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>M4 People</td>\n      <td>2.8</td>\n      <td>Amber</td>\n      <td>3</td>\n      <td>HR documentation and performance reviews infrequent; recruitment and retention processes underdeveloped.</td>\n      <td>Review and update position descriptions and implement a quarterly performance review schedule.</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>M2 Legal, Compliance &amp; Property</td>\n      <td>3.0</td>\n      <td>Amber</td>\n      <td>4</td>\n      <td>Legal and property compliance gaps around SLAs and property upgrades need attention.</td>\n      <td>Audit and renew all third-party SLAs and schedule property condition assessments.</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>M5 Customer, Product &amp; Revenue Quality</td>\n      <td>3.0</td>\n      <td>Amber</td>\n      <td>5</td>\n      <td>Lack of margin benchmarking and no formal sales/marketing plan pose product strategy risks.</td>\n      <td>Benchmark product margins against industry standards and draft a basic sales and marketing plan.</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>M3 Owner Dependency &amp; Operations</td>\n      <td>3.4</td>\n      <td>Amber</td>\n      <td>6</td>\n      <td>High owner dependency (70%) and limited governance structures create continuity risk.</td>\n      <td>Develop succession and backup plans for key owner duties to reduce single-person risk.</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>M1 Financial Clarity &amp; Reporting</td>\n      <td>3.8</td>\n      <td>Green</td>\n      <td>7</td>\n      <td>Strong financial controls but quarterly reporting limits timeliness of insights.</td>\n      <td>Increase financial report review frequency from quarterly to monthly.</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>M7 Tax, Compliance &amp; Regulatory</td>\n      <td>5.0</td>\n      <td>Green</td>\n      <td>8</td>\n      <td>Tax and activity statements fully up to date, demonstrating strong compliance.</td>\n      <td>Maintain current lodgement schedules and collate ATO records for buyer review.</td>\n    </tr>\n  </table>\n\n  <h1>Advisor Report</h1>\n\n  <h2>1. Executive summary</h2>\n  <p>\n    Chris, Greenside Outdoor Living Pty Ltd is a 27-year-old outdoor furniture manufacturer generating AUD 5–10 million in turnover. Founders Alan and Kate Turner are preparing to retire. The business exhibits robust profitability, up-to-date licences and tax compliance, and solid operational processes. To maximise valuation and buyer confidence, priority actions include establishing consistent brand guidelines, updating the strategic plan, strengthening HR documentation and performance reviews, consolidating legal and property compliance, and formalising sales and marketing processes.\n  </p>\n\n  <h2>2. Module findings</h2>\n  <h3>M1 Financial Clarity &amp; Reporting</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Key financial reports (P&amp;L, balance sheet, cash flow forecast) reviewed only quarterly.</li>\n        <li>Meetings with the accountant occur quarterly, limiting timely insights.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Bookkeeper in place ensures accurate records.</li>\n        <li>Business generated a profit last year; BAS and tax returns are current.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M2 Legal, Compliance &amp; Property</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Service level and other third-party agreements not centrally consolidated.</li>\n        <li>No formal legal compliance audit or documented process.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>All licences are current and no legal actions are pending.</li>\n        <li>Property lease terms are well documented.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M3 Owner Dependency &amp; Operations</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Business relies on owners for 70% of operations with no succession plan.</li>\n        <li>No board or formal governance structure in place.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Divisional and team meetings occur regularly and processes are documented.</li>\n        <li>Technology systems are integrated and supported by IT providers.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M4 People</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Position descriptions were last reviewed over two years ago.</li>\n        <li>Performance reviews conducted only every six months.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>HR policies and procedures are established and HR metrics are tracked.</li>\n        <li>Team cohesion is strong and there are no under-performing staff.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M5 Customer, Product &amp; Revenue Quality</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>No formal sales and marketing plan; marketing ROI not tracked.</li>\n        <li>Profit margins are not benchmarked; top three customers account for 50% of revenue.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Sales strategy exists and customer segmentation is clearly defined.</li>\n        <li>CRM system in place and product reviews occur annually.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M6 Brand, IP &amp; Intangibles</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>No formal brand style guide; website updates occur only annually.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Website is live and refreshed within the last 12 months.</li>\n        <li>Physical premises require no immediate external upgrades.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M7 Tax, Compliance &amp; Regulatory</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>None identified.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Activity statements and tax returns are fully up to date.</li>\n        <li>Compliance processes are robust and can be readily audited.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Concerns:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Strategic business plan not reviewed for over two years.</li>\n        <li>No international trading plan in place.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li>Opportunities:\n      <ul>\n        <li>Strategic plan exists and can be refreshed quickly.</li>\n        <li>Some due diligence documents (financials, licences, leases) are already prepared.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h2>3. Module scores &amp; RAG ranking</h2>\n  <table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n    <tr>\n      <th>Module</th>\n      <th>Score</th>\n      <th>RAG</th>\n      <th>Rank</th>\n    </tr>\n    <tr><td>M6 Brand, IP &amp; Intangibles</td><td>2.5</td><td>Amber</td><td>1</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</td><td>2.7</td><td>Amber</td><td>2</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>M4 People</td><td>2.8</td><td>Amber</td><td>3</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>M2 Legal, Compliance &amp; Property</td><td>3.0</td><td>Amber</td><td>4</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>M5 Customer, Product &amp; Revenue Quality</td><td>3.0</td><td>Amber</td><td>5</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>M3 Owner Dependency &amp; Operations</td><td>3.4</td><td>Amber</td><td>6</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>M1 Financial Clarity &amp; Reporting</td><td>3.8</td><td>Green</td><td>7</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>M7 Tax, Compliance &amp; Regulatory</td><td>5.0</td><td>Green</td><td>8</td></tr>\n  </table>\n\n  <h2>4. Task list by module</h2>\n\n  <h3>M1 Financial Clarity &amp; Reporting</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Establish a monthly reporting calendar for P&amp;L, balance sheet, cash flow and inventory metrics.</li>\n    <li>Increase the frequency of accountant meetings from quarterly to monthly.</li>\n    <li>Maintain and verify all BAS and income-tax lodgements are current.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M2 Legal, Compliance &amp; Property</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Conduct a legal compliance audit covering all licences and third-party agreements.</li>\n    <li>Consolidate supplier, customer and contractor contracts in a central repository.</li>\n    <li>Schedule a property condition assessment ahead of the next lease review.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M3 Owner Dependency &amp; Operations</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Develop a succession and delegation plan for critical owner responsibilities.</li>\n    <li>Document all key processes and assign owners for regular reviews.</li>\n    <li>Implement governance by forming a board or advisory committee.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M4 People</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Review and update all position descriptions at least annually.</li>\n    <li>Implement a quarterly performance review framework for staff and contractors.</li>\n    <li>Create an HR dashboard to monitor absenteeism, turnover and leave balances.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M5 Customer, Product &amp; Revenue Quality</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Draft and document a formal sales and marketing plan aligned to strategic objectives.</li>\n    <li>Implement ROI tracking for all marketing activities.</li>\n    <li>Benchmark product margins against industry standards and adjust pricing accordingly.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M6 Brand, IP &amp; Intangibles</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Develop and approve a comprehensive brand style guide covering logos, fonts and communications.</li>\n    <li>Schedule quarterly reviews of brand assets and website content for consistency.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M7 Tax, Compliance &amp; Regulatory</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Maintain lodgement and payment schedules for BAS, IAS and income-tax obligations.</li>\n    <li>Conduct quarterly reviews of regulatory registers and compliance documentation.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Assemble a central due diligence data room with financials, licences, leases and key contracts.</li>\n    <li>Review and refresh the strategic business plan within the next month.</li>\n    <li>Create a draft international trading plan for buyer review.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h2>5. Additional bespoke tasks</h2>\n  <p>No additional bespoke tasks identified at this stage.</p>\n</body>\n</html>','red','diagnostic','2025-07-07 02:35:50','2025-07-07 02:35:50'),(25,3,NULL,'Diagnostic Advice',1,0,'<html>\n  <body>\n    <h1>1. Executive Summary</h1>\n    <p>Manuco Pty Ltd, a 23-year-old roofing products manufacturer under eight years of current ownership, is experiencing declining financial performance and significant owner dependency. While tax and regulatory compliance are robust, key gaps exist in financial reporting, operational documentation, HR processes and sales & marketing. This report prioritises eight Sale-Ready modules, with immediate focus on Financial Clarity & Reporting (M1) and Due Diligence Preparation (M8), followed by People (M4), Customer, Product & Revenue Quality (M5), Legal, Compliance & Property (M2), Owner Dependency & Operations (M3), Brand, IP & Intangibles (M6) and ongoing Tax, Compliance & Regulatory maintenance (M7).</p>\n\n    <h1>2. Module Findings</h1>\n    <h2>M1 Financial Clarity & Reporting</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Concern: Overall loss last year, reliance on overdraft and debt, inability to meet repayments.</li>\n      <li>Concern: Financial reports reviewed only quarterly; accountant meetings once per year.</li>\n      <li>Opportunity: Bookkeeper in place; optimistic about turnaround.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h2>M2 Legal, Compliance & Property</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Concern: Licences are expired; property requires boardroom paint and roof repairs.</li>\n      <li>Opportunity: No outstanding legal actions; SLAs with third parties exist.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h2>M3 Owner Dependency & Operations</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Concern: 80 % owner reliance, key processes undocumented, low operational reporting.</li>\n      <li>Opportunity: Board, divisional structure and succession plan exist; ERP system in use.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h2>M4 People</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Concern: Under-performing staff, no one-on-one reviews, risk of losing key employees.</li>\n      <li>Opportunity: HR policies in place; HR data (absenteeism, leave) measured.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h2>M5 Customer, Product & Revenue Quality</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Concern: Product/service review over one year overdue; margins below industry; no sales & marketing plan; weak CRM use.</li>\n      <li>Opportunity: Prices updated three months ago; customers understand offerings; custom solutions differentiate.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h2>M6 Brand, IP & Intangibles</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Concern: No style guide; premises need external facelift.</li>\n      <li>Opportunity: Website current; branding consistency across channels rated 10/10.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h2>M7 Tax, Compliance & Regulatory</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Opportunity: BAS, business tax returns and activity statements are up to date.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h2>M8 Due Diligence Preparation</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Concern: Strategic business plan review date unknown; no international trading plan.</li>\n      <li>Opportunity: Plan exists; data-room structure can be created swiftly.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h1>3. Task List by Module (Standard Library Tasks)</h1>\n    <h2>M1 Financial Clarity & Reporting</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Implement monthly profit & loss review meetings.</li>\n      <li>Develop a rolling 12-month cash flow forecasting model.</li>\n      <li>Automate P&L and balance sheet reporting.</li>\n      <li>Maintain a consolidated debt register.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h2>M2 Legal, Compliance & Property</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Ensure all licences and permits are current and reviewed annually.</li>\n      <li>Conduct an annual legal compliance audit.</li>\n      <li>Review property lease and maintenance agreements.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h2>M3 Owner Dependency & Operations</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Document core business processes and procedures.</li>\n      <li>Schedule monthly operational performance reviews.</li>\n      <li>Optimise ERP workflows and user training.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h2>M4 People</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Update and standardise position descriptions.</li>\n      <li>Implement bi-annual performance review cycles.</li>\n      <li>Develop a succession and retention plan for key roles.</li>\n 