INSERT INTO `tasks` VALUES (1,4,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Document Core Business Processes','1. List all key activities for workshops, 1:1 coaching and back-office tasks.\n2. Schedule three 2-hour sessions with Laura to capture step-by-step procedures.\n3. Draft Standard Operating Procedures (SOP) in a consistent template.\n4. Review each SOP with Laura and refine.\n5. Store finalized SOPs in a shared online folder with version control.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:48:14','2025-05-26 21:48:14'),(2,4,NULL,NULL,0,'due-diligence','Develop Succession & Business Continuity Plan','1. Identify at least two potential internal or external candidates to cover Laura’s duties.\n2. Define critical tasks and decision points in an owner-absent scenario.\n3. Create a simple continuity flowchart and escalation contacts list.\n4. Draft a one-page succession summary to include in investor or buyer pitch materials.\n5. Review and finalize plan with Laura and legal advisor.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:48:14','2025-05-26 21:48:14'),(3,4,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Establish CRM & Customer Data Tracking','1. Research and shortlist two CRM platforms that fit under $100/month.\n2. Import existing customer list (25 active clients) and segment into schools, repeat vs new.\n3. Create fields for campaign source, follow-up dates and ROI tracking.\n4. Train Laura or an assistant on basic CRM operations in a 1-hour session.\n5. Set up automated reminders for client follow-ups and quarterly reviews.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:48:14','2025-05-26 21:48:14'),(4,4,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Define Organizational Structure & Support Roles','1. Map current activities Laura performs daily and weekly.\n2. Identify at least three outsourced or part-time roles (e.g. admin, marketing, co-facilitator).\n3. Draft job descriptions for each role with responsibilities and hours required.\n4. Post roles on two freelance platforms and contact three allied coaches for co-facilitation.\n5. Schedule interviews and negotiate terms to onboard at least one contractor.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:48:14','2025-05-26 21:48:14'),(5,4,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Premises Upgrade Action Plan','1. Walk through 7 Oakland Court and list required upgrades (paint, signage, furniture).\n2. Obtain three quotes from local contractors for each upgrade item.\n3. Compare quotes, verify contractor insurance and lead times.\n4. Approve a budget and schedule works during non-peak hours.\n5. Oversee installation and conduct a post-upgrade walkthrough.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:48:14','2025-05-26 21:48:14'),(6,4,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Research Federal Anti-Bullying Grants & Prepare Proposal','1. Identify two relevant state or federal grant programs with upcoming deadlines.\n2. Review eligibility criteria and required documentation.\n3. Draft program alignment narrative highlighting Laura’s expertise and past results.\n4. Compile financials, letters of support and draft budget sheets.\n5. Submit full proposal at least five days before each deadline.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:48:14','2025-05-26 21:48:14'),(7,4,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Develop Targeted Sales & Marketing Plan','1. Define three school decision-maker personas (e.g. Principal, Guidance Officer, PTA Lead).\n2. Set SMART goals: number of new schools, repeat rate targets, campaign ROI.\n3. Outline a 90-day marketing calendar with email, social media, webinars.\n4. Draft messaging leveraging Laura’s passion and results; align with anti-bullying grant themes.\n5. Establish weekly review meetings to track campaign metrics and adjust tactics.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:48:14','2025-05-26 21:48:14'),(8,4,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Implement Financial Management & Bookkeeping Infrastructure','1. Engage a qualified bookkeeper to record all transactions in Xero by week 2.\n2. Set up a dashboard for monthly P&L, cash-flow and ATO debt tracking.\n3. Schedule monthly reviews with Accountant Scott Price and update forecast variances.\n4. Establish a payment schedule to clear the $8,995 ATO debt by November 2025.\n5. Create a simple expense approval process for travel and premises costs.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:48:14','2025-05-26 21:48:14'),(9,4,NULL,NULL,0,'tax','Engage Bookkeeper & Review Tax Compliance','1. Research and select a local bookkeeper experienced with trusts and small edu-services.\n2. Set up monthly bookkeeping deliverables and communication protocols.\n3. Confirm all Activity Statements and Business Tax Returns are filed and up to date.\n4. Ask bookkeeper to prepare a 12-month tax obligation calendar.\n5. Meet with Scott Price to review any tax minimisation strategies under the family trust.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:48:14','2025-05-26 21:48:14'),(10,4,NULL,NULL,0,'competitive-forces','Perform Competitor & Market Analysis','1. List four main direct competitors and three potential new entrants.\n2. For each, document service offerings, pricing, strengths and weaknesses.\n3. Identify barriers to entry and emerging threats like reseller programs.\n4. Update Laura’s unique value proposition to differentiate on depth and outcomes.\n5. Produce a one-page competitive matrix to inform marketing and pricing decisions.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:48:14','2025-05-26 21:48:14'),(11,1,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Evaluate and Select a CRM Platform','James should research at least three CRM vendors (e.g., HubSpot, Zoho, Pipedrive). For each option: schedule demos, request pricing quotes, list must-have features (contact segmentation, pipeline tracking, KPI dashboards), and evaluate integration capabilities with Make.com, Zapier and QuickBooks. Present findings in a comparison matrix and select the best fit.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:49:32','2025-05-26 21:49:32'),(12,1,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Migrate Customer Data into the New CRM','Export all customer records from existing spreadsheets and QuickBooks. Clean and standardize fields (names, emails, company). Use the CRM’s import tool or CSV templates to upload data. Run a sample import, validate records, then complete full migration. Document the import process in a one-page SOP.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:49:32','2025-05-26 21:49:32'),(13,1,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Segment Customer Lists and Configure CRM Dashboards','Define three segments (existing clients, lapsed clients, new prospects). In the CRM, create tags or lists for each. Build dashboard widgets for pipeline value, new-client conversion rate, and follow-up tasks. Set automated email sequences for each segment with templated messaging.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:49:32','2025-05-26 21:49:32'),(14,1,NULL,NULL,0,'competitive-forces','Develop a Detailed Sales and Marketing Plan','Draft a two-page plan outlining target SME sectors, ideal customer profiles, value propositions, and channel mix (LinkedIn, SEO, content). Define monthly lead and revenue targets. Establish a timeline for campaign launches, budget allocations, and quarterly review checkpoints.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:49:32','2025-05-26 21:49:32'),(15,1,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Recruit an In-House Sales Representative','Write a job description covering roles, KPIs, commission structure and required experience. Post on LinkedIn, industry job boards and referral networks. Screen resumes, conduct at least three interviews, and make an offer. Aim to complete hiring and onboarding within 30 days.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:49:32','2025-05-26 21:49:32'),(16,1,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Document Core Operational Workflows','Map and write step-by-step SOPs for development support, hosting support and client onboarding. Use flowcharts or numbered procedures. Store all documents in a shared drive or wiki. Review each workflow with any involved contractors for accuracy.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:49:32','2025-05-26 21:49:32'),(17,1,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Draft and Implement HR Policies and Procedures','Research sample small-business HR manuals. Draft policies for leave, performance reviews, onboarding/offboarding and code of conduct. Circulate a draft to Farrah and key contractors for feedback. Finalise the manual and communicate new policies to all team members.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:49:32','2025-05-26 21:49:32'),(18,1,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Conduct a Pricing Review and Margin Analysis','Compile the last 12 months of billing data by service. Benchmark rates against three competitors. Identify under-priced services and propose new rate cards, including premium tiers. Present margin improvement opportunities to the accountant for feedback.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:49:32','2025-05-26 21:49:32'),(19,1,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Automate Support Tickets and Billing Processes','List repetitive tasks (ticket creation, billing reminders). In Make.com or Zapier, build workflows to generate tickets from emails, update billing status, and send invoice reminders. Test each automation in a sandbox environment, then deploy to production. Document automation flows.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:49:32','2025-05-26 21:49:32'),(20,1,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Launch Targeted LinkedIn and SEO Campaigns','Define campaign goals (e.g., 10 new leads/month). Create LinkedIn ad creatives targeting SME decision-makers. Conduct keyword research and update on-page SEO. Set up lead-capture forms and integrate with CRM. Monitor metrics weekly and optimize bids and content.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:49:32','2025-05-26 21:49:32'),(21,1,NULL,NULL,0,'general','Draft a Formal Succession and Continuity Plan','List all CEO/GM duties James performs. Identify internal or external candidates for each role. Define a transition timeline and training schedule. Document key client-relationship handovers and emergency procedures. Review draft plan with Farrah for approval.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:49:32','2025-05-26 21:49:32'),(22,1,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Review and Update Client Service Contracts for Retainer Models','Gather existing service agreements. Draft new contract templates introducing tiered retainer packages and SLAs. Have a legal advisor review terms. Finalise and distribute to top three clients for upsell conversations.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:49:32','2025-05-26 21:49:32'),(23,1,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Engage a Bookkeeper and Schedule Monthly Financial Reviews','Research local or virtual bookkeeping services. Request proposals and select one. Set up access to QuickBooks and bank feeds. Schedule a recurring monthly meeting with Chakra Shamnani to review P&L, Balance Sheet and cash-flow projections.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:49:32','2025-05-26 21:49:32'),(24,1,NULL,NULL,0,'due-diligence','Prepare Due-Diligence Documentation for Future Sale','Collect the last three years of financial statements, contracts, SOPs and customer lists. Organise them into labelled folders in a secure cloud repository. Create an index document summarising each file for easy navigation by potential buyers or advisors.',NULL,0,'low',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:49:32','2025-05-26 21:49:32'),(25,1,NULL,NULL,0,'diagnostic','Set Up Weekly Delegation Meetings and Task Tracking','Block a 60-minute recurring weekly meeting in James’ calendar. Invite any key contractors or staff. Prepare a standard agenda template (status updates, blockers, action items). Use a project management tool (e.g., Trello or Asana) to assign and track tasks and reduce James’s operational load.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:49:32','2025-05-26 21:49:32'),(26,1,NULL,NULL,0,'tax','Schedule a Quarterly Tax Planning Meeting','Contact Chakra at Jungle Books to book a tax planning session within the next 30 days. Prepare year-to-date financial summaries and estimated quarterly liabilities. Discuss any available deductions, S Corp distribution strategies and upcoming deadlines.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-26 21:49:32','2025-05-26 21:49:32'),(27,3,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Renew Critical Operating Licences','1. Gather existing licence documents (manufacturing, roofing, safety). 2. Verify expiry dates and fee requirements. 3. Complete renewal applications and attach required insurance certificates. 4. Submit to relevant regulators and confirm receipt. 5. Track application status and follow up weekly until approved.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-02 20:01:37','2025-06-02 20:01:37'),(28,3,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Conduct Supplier Renegotiation Sessions','1. List top 10 suppliers by spend. 2. Request updated pricing, volume discounts and extended payment terms. 3. Schedule negotiation meetings over next two weeks. 4. Document agreed terms and update purchase contracts. 5. Monitor post-renegotiation invoices to ensure compliance.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-02 20:01:37','2025-06-02 20:01:37'),(29,3,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Implement Cost Reduction Plan','1. Extract last 12 months’ expense reports from Xero. 2. Identify discretionary spend >5% of revenue. 3. Propose cost-cutting measures (e.g. reduce casual staffing hours, pause non-essential subscriptions). 4. Present plan to owners and secure approval. 5. Assign cost-owners and track savings weekly.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-02 20:01:37','2025-06-02 20:01:37'),(30,3,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Define and Document Sales Process','1. Map current sales steps from lead generation to close. 2. Define pipeline stages and entry/exit criteria. 3. Create a sales playbook template with scripts and responsibilities. 4. Validate playbook with two top performers. 5. Distribute final document and train sales team by day 30.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-02 20:01:37','2025-06-02 20:01:37'),(31,3,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Deploy and Configure CRM for ROI Tracking','1. Audit Infusionsoft data fields and sales stages. 2. Define key metrics (lead source, conversion rate, deal value). 3. Build CRM dashboards and custom reports. 4. Train staff in data entry standards and report interpretation. 5. Schedule weekly review of campaign ROI.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-02 20:01:37','2025-06-02 20:01:37'),(32,3,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Launch Quarterly Performance Review Process','1. Draft performance review templates covering KPIs, behaviours and development goals. 2. Schedule 1:1 meetings with all staff over next 4 weeks. 3. Train managers on feedback best practices. 4. Complete initial reviews and document outcomes in HR system. 5. Define follow-up actions and training plans.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-02 20:01:37','2025-06-02 20:01:37'),(33,3,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Update and Standardise Job Descriptions','1. Collect existing JD documents for all roles. 2. Identify missing or outdated descriptions. 3. Interview each role owner to capture key duties and skills. 4. Draft updated JDs and circulate for feedback. 5. Publish final versions to HR folder and communicate to staff.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-02 20:01:37','2025-06-02 20:01:37'),(34,3,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Develop Owner Delegation and Continuity Plan','1. List all owner-dependent tasks and responsibilities. 2. Identify capable deputies for each area. 3. Document step-by-step handover procedures. 4. Schedule shadowing sessions for deputies. 5. Test handover by having owner step back for one day.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-02 20:01:37','2025-06-02 20:01:37'),(35,3,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Stock Reduction and Working Capital Release','1. Run stock report and identify slow-moving lines (12+ months unsold). 2. Categorise items for markdown, return to supplier or liquidation. 3. Set weekly clearance targets to hit $125K stock level. 4. Monitor stock-value daily in ERP. 5. Reconcile physical counts at month end.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-02 20:01:37','2025-06-02 20:01:37'),(36,3,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Implement WIP Age Controls','1. Extract WIP report and sort by age. 2. Set maximum age threshold of 3 days per order. 3. Assign daily WIP review owner and meeting cadence. 4. Escalate orders exceeding threshold to production manager. 5. Record corrective actions and track time-to-close.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-02 20:01:37','2025-06-02 20:01:37'),(37,3,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Assess ERP and CRM Integration Needs','1. Document current data flows between Xero, Infusionsoft and ERP. 2. Identify manual reconciliation tasks and data gaps. 3. Engage IT support provider to propose integration options. 4. Obtain cost and timeline estimates. 5. Prioritise integration tasks for next quarter.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-02 20:01:37','2025-06-02 20:01:37'),(38,3,NULL,NULL,0,'general','Research E-Commerce Platform Feasibility','1. List 3 e-commerce platforms (e.g. Shopify, WooCommerce, BigCommerce). 2. Compare setup costs, transaction fees and integrations. 3. Interview two peers who implemented online sales. 4. Draft costs/benefits summary. 5. Present recommendation to owners.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-02 20:01:37','2025-06-02 20:01:37'),(39,3,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Customer Diversification Strategy','1. Export customer list from CRM and segment top 10% by revenue. 2. Identify 5 new target industries or regions. 3. Assign lead generation tasks to sales reps. 4. Develop prospect outreach templates. 5. Set weekly prospecting goal and review progress.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-02 20:01:37','2025-06-02 20:01:37'),(40,3,NULL,NULL,0,'due-diligence','Prepare Due-Diligence Data Room','1. Collate last three years of audited financials. 2. Include licence and compliance certificates. 3. Gather property and lease agreements. 4. Assemble key customer and supplier contracts. 5. Store all documents in secure shared folder and index contents.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-02 20:01:37','2025-06-02 20:01:37'),(41,3,NULL,NULL,0,'tax','Schedule Tax and BAS Review with Accountant','1. Book a meeting with Forsyths within 2 weeks. 2. Prepare up-to-date P&L, balance sheet and BAS statements. 3. Discuss optimisation of tax position and debt structure. 4. Agree on quarterly review schedule going forward. 5. Document action items and deadlines.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-02 20:01:37','2025-06-02 20:01:37'),(42,3,NULL,NULL,0,'competitive-forces','Conduct Competitor Analysis Update','1. Review and update profiles of four main competitors. 2. Document recent price changes, product launches and market moves. 3. Identify any emerging overseas entrants. 4. Summarise threats/opportunities in one-page report. 5. Share insights at next strategy meeting.',NULL,0,'low',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-02 20:01:37','2025-06-02 20:01:37'),(43,3,NULL,NULL,0,'diagnostic','Review and Update Documented Processes','1. List all documented processes and procedures. 2. Assign process owners to review accuracy. 3. Schedule review sessions and capture updates. 4. Version control final documents in central repository. 5. Communicate review completion and next review date.',NULL,0,'low',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-02 20:01:37','2025-06-02 20:01:37'),(44,3,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Renew Critical Licences and Certificates','By day 15, collate current licence details (Manuf Licence expiring 12/06/2025 and Safety Certificate expiring 01/05/2025). Complete renewal applications, arrange approvals, pay fees ($8,000 and $5,263 respectively) and update internal licence registry. Confirm confirmation emails are received and file digital copies.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-03 01:52:14','2025-06-03 01:52:14'),(45,3,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Conduct Full Legal Compliance Audit','Engage external legal advisor to review building industry code obligations and your lease (expires 12/12/2025). Document any non-compliance items, schedule remediation tasks, and prepare a compliance register by day 30.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-03 01:52:14','2025-06-03 01:52:14'),(46,3,NULL,NULL,0,'due-diligence','Review and Update Strategic Business Plan','Gather last strategic plan, financial forecasts and industry research. Host a half-day workshop with key stakeholders (Stacey, Mary, senior managers) in week 2 to refresh vision, objectives and key metrics. Distribute updated plan for sign-off by day 30.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-03 01:52:14','2025-06-03 01:52:14'),(47,3,NULL,NULL,0,'due-diligence','Develop International Trading Framework','Draft an outline covering target markets, compliance requirements, logistics partners and pricing strategy. Assign research tasks to team members and review progress in weekly check-ins. Finalise framework draft by day 30.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-03 01:52:14','2025-06-03 01:52:14'),(48,3,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Implement Monthly Financial Review Cadence','Set calendar invites for a monthly finance meeting. Prepare a standard report pack including P&L, cash-flow, balance sheet, stock levels and WIP. First meeting to take place by day 30 with your bookkeeper and accountant (Forsyths).',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-03 01:52:14','2025-06-03 01:52:14'),(49,3,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Schedule Quarterly Accountant Check-In','Contact Bob Hope at Forsyths to schedule a 1-hour strategy meeting in month 3. Outline agenda: variance analysis, cost drivers (contractors, staff), and recovery plan for $50k–$100k net loss.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-03 01:52:14','2025-06-03 01:52:14'),(50,3,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Automate Weekly Operational Reporting','Engage IT support to configure ERP dashboards (currently rated 1/10) for equipment utilisation, team utilisation, stock levels and forward orders. Pilot daily dashboard by day 20 and transition to weekly automated distribution to managers.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-03 01:52:14','2025-06-03 01:52:14'),(51,3,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Plan and Launch Monthly Management Meetings','Create recurring agenda and minutes template. Invite senior management from both divisions and owners. Cover KPIs, risk register, compliance status and strategic progress. First meeting to be held by day 30.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-03 01:52:14','2025-06-03 01:52:14'),(52,3,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Update Position Descriptions and Succession Tasks','Collect current job descriptions for all key roles. Revise duties, reporting lines, required skills and update via HR system. Draft succession plan steps for Stacey and Mary’s roles. Complete updates by day 30.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-03 01:52:14','2025-06-03 01:52:14'),(53,3,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Design Quarterly Performance Review Process','Develop a simple review form. Schedule Q1 reviews for all staff and contractors. Train managers on feedback delivery. Launch process by end of month 1.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-03 01:52:14','2025-06-03 01:52:14'),(54,3,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Create Sales & Marketing Plan with ROI Tracking','Map current spend ($10k–$25k offline/online), define target segments, draft 6-month campaign calendar and assign budget. Implement ROI tracking in CRM and schedule weekly data reviews. Plan to be finalised by day 30.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-03 01:52:14','2025-06-03 01:52:14'),(55,3,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Establish Customer Diversification Strategy','Analyze top 3 clients (52% revenue) and list next 10 prospects. Develop incentives (discounts, service contracts) to onboard at least 2 new customers within 30 days. Assign sales reps and monitor weekly progress.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-03 01:52:14','2025-06-03 01:52:14'),(56,3,NULL,NULL,0,'competitive-forces','Update Competitive Analysis and Risk Register','Review current competitor profiles (Manuf R Us, Clins Manuf). Document barriers to entry, supplier and buyer threats. Add findings to risk register and schedule mitigation actions in next management meeting.',NULL,0,'low',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-03 01:52:14','2025-06-03 01:52:14'),(57,3,NULL,NULL,0,'tax','Confirm Tax Lodgement Schedules','Review next BAS and tax return due dates. Confirm all activity statements and returns are up to date. Set reminders for upcoming lodgements and assign responsibility.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-03 01:52:14','2025-06-03 01:52:14'),(58,3,NULL,NULL,0,'general','Kick-off 30-Day Progress Review','Schedule a 60-minute meeting with Peter Spinda, Stacey, Mary and key stakeholders at day 30. Review completion status of all tasks, update RAG ratings and adjust priorities for month 2.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-03 01:52:14','2025-06-03 01:52:14'),(59,3,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Renew Manufacturing Licence','1. Confirm current licence status and identify lapses. 2. Gather required safety records, insurance certificates and supporting documents. 3. Contact the regulatory body by phone or online portal. 4. Submit renewal application, upload documentation and pay the $8,000 fee. 5. Track application status daily until approval, and file renewal confirmation in the central compliance folder.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-13 02:19:28','2025-06-13 02:19:28'),(60,3,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Renew Safety Certificate','1. Review last safety audit report and note outstanding actions. 2. Schedule a site inspection with an accredited auditor. 3. Complete corrective actions before inspection date. 4. Submit safety certificate renewal application and pay the $5,263 fee. 5. File the renewed certificate in the compliance binder and set calendar reminders six months before next expiry.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-13 02:19:28','2025-06-13 02:19:28'),(61,3,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Formalise Service-Level Agreements with Contractors','1. List all third-party contractors and current informal arrangements. 2. Draft standard service-level agreement template including scope, KPIs, pricing and termination clauses. 3. Review draft with legal advisor. 4. Send agreements to each contractor for signature. 5. Store signed SLAs in the contract management system and assign renewal reminders.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-13 02:19:28','2025-06-13 02:19:28'),(62,3,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Audit and Document Lease Terms','1. Retrieve the lease agreement for 8 Gregsue Ct and any related amendments. 2. Verify current term expiry (12/12/2025) and option periods. 3. Document rent, outgoings, review methods and notice periods in a central register. 4. Flag next review date (10/11/2025) and assign responsibility. 5. Save all lease documents in the propert