,'2025-06-18 00:45:51','2025-06-18 00:45:51'),(204,9,NULL,NULL,0,'tax','Review Tax Planning for Upcoming Sale','1. Meet with accountant (Tracey Vinn) to run capital gains tax scenarios. 2. Identify opportunities for small business CGT concessions. 3. Document tax election deadlines and requirements. 4. Implement any trust or shareholding structures recommended. 5. File necessary elections before the sale listing.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:45:51','2025-06-18 00:45:51'),(205,10,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Conduct detailed inventory audit and liquidation plan','1. Export current stock report from NetSuite and compare against the $650k manageable threshold. 2. Identify slow‐moving and obsolete SKUs representing the excess $550k. 3. Develop targeted promotions or bundling strategies with the marketing team. 4. Execute weekly stock clearance events and track cash inflows daily. 5. Report progress against the $550k cash‐release goal at the end of each week.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:56:18','2025-06-18 00:56:18'),(206,10,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Negotiate ANZ mortgage restructure and lease refinancing','1. Gather current repayment schedules for the $2.1m ANZ mortgage and $390k equipment lease. 2. Schedule a meeting with ANZ relationship manager within 7 days to discuss interest rate reductions or term extensions. 3. Model revised repayment scenarios in NetSuite to assess monthly cash‐flow impact. 4. Finalise and execute amended facility agreements by day 30.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:56:18','2025-06-18 00:56:18'),(207,10,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Kick‐off CRM replacement project','1. Document current CRM shortcomings and desired features. 2. Identify and shortlist 3 potential CRM vendors within 10 days. 3. Prepare and issue a request for proposal (RFP) to shortlisted vendors. 4. Assemble a cross‐functional evaluation team (Sales, Marketing, IT) and score proposals. 5. Present vendor recommendation to the executive team by day 30.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:56:18','2025-06-18 00:56:18'),(208,10,NULL,NULL,0,'due-diligence','Prepare sale‐readiness data room and governance pack','1. Collect audited financial statements, bank facilities letters, lease agreements, licence documents (TGA, AICIS, EPA), and corporate governance records. 2. Organise documents into a secure online data room structure. 3. Draft an executive summary and governance presentation for prospective buyers. 4. Review for completeness with the accountant and legal advisor. 5. Ensure all documents are uploaded and access permissions set by day 30.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:56:18','2025-06-18 00:56:18'),(209,10,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Review and update corporate governance and shareholder agreements','1. Engage your corporate lawyer to review the current shareholder agreement, board minutes and succession plan. 2. Update any outdated clauses, particularly around share transfer and exit timelines. 3. Host a board meeting to approve amendments and capture minutes. 4. File updated documents with ASIC if required. 5. Complete all legal filings by day 30.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:56:18','2025-06-18 00:56:18'),(210,10,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Map production workflows and eliminate WIP bottlenecks','1. Convene an operations workshop with production supervisors to map current WIP flows. 2. Identify stages where work stays unfinished over three days. 3. Analyse root causes (staffing, equipment downtime, process gaps). 4. Define and implement 2–3 process improvements (e.g. parallel batching, shift adjustments). 5. Track WIP age daily and aim to reduce unfinished jobs to under 24 hours by day 30.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:56:18','2025-06-18 00:56:18'),(211,10,NULL,NULL,0,'general','Initiate US market entry feasibility 