0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:56:18','2025-06-18 00:56:18'),(215,10,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Clean up existing CRM data and train current users','1. Export key customer data from HubSpot and identify duplicates and incomplete records. 2. Assign an operations resource to merge duplicates and fill missing fields. 3. Develop and deliver a 2-hour CRM best-practice training session for Sales and CS teams. 4. Establish weekly data quality checks to maintain system hygiene. 5. Report data health improvements at month‐end.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:56:18','2025-06-18 00:56:18'),(216,10,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Optimize Inventory Levels','1. Export current inventory report from NetSuite. 2. Identify top 20 slow-moving SKUs and calculate their carrying cost. 3. Develop promotional or bundled sales campaigns to clear at least $550,000 of excess stock. 4. Adjust reorder points in the system to maintain a maximum of $650,000 stock on hand. 5. Review inventory levels weekly and adjust tactics.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:57:42','2025-06-18 00:57:42'),(217,10,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Accelerate Debt Repayment Plan','1. Gather current ANZ mortgage and equipment lease statements. 2. Schedule a meeting with ANZ and lease provider to discuss options for accelerated principal repayments or refinancing. 3. Prepare cash-flow forecasts to demonstrate capacity for increased payments. 4. Agree on a revised repayment schedule and document new terms.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:57:42','2025-06-18 00:57:42'),(218,10,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Review Equipment Lease Financing','1. Retrieve full lease agreements and amortization schedules. 2. Analyze cost of early buy-out versus remaining lease payments. 3. Contact the lessor to negotiate lower rates or early purchase options. 4. Present options to the finance committee and decide by month end.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:57:42','2025-06-18 00:57:42'),(219,10,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Upgrade CRM System','1. Audit current HubSpot usage and list missing features preventing 10/10 performance. 2. Define detailed CRM requirements: loyalty scheme, subscription management, customer segmentation. 3. Shortlist at least three CRM solutions (e.g. HubSpot Advanced, Salesforce, Zoho). 4. Schedule demos with each vendor. 5. Develop implementation timeline and budget for board approval.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:57:42','2025-06-18 00:57:42'),(220,10,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Analyze Production Bottlenecks','1. Map end-to-end production workflow in NetSuite and on the factory floor. 2. Tag work-in-progress (WIP) items older than three days. 3. Conduct root-cause analysis with operations team using Ishikawa or 5 Whys. 4. Document findings and propose process changes (e.g. resource reallocation, layout adjustments).',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:57:42','2025-06-18 00:57:42'),(221,10,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Implement WIP Cycle Improvements','1. Set a daily WIP age report in NetSuite and export at 8am each day. 2. Assign a process owner for each production line to monitor WIP flow. 3. Define target: no item older than one day in any WIP bin. 4. Hold daily 15-minute stand-up to review WIP deviations and assign corrective actions.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:57:42','2025-06-18 00:57:42'),(222,10,NULL,NULL,0,'due-diligence','Prepare Sale Due-Diligence Pack','1. Collate audited financial statements for last 3 years and management accounts. 2. Gather corporate governance documents: board minutes, shareholder agreements, succession plan. 3. Compile license certificates (TGA, AICIS, EPA) and renewal records. 4. Assemble key contracts: supply, lease, customer contracts. 5. Store all files in a secure virtual dataroom.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:57:42','2025-06-18 00:57:42'),(223,10,NULL,NULL,0,'due-diligence','Conduct US Market Regulatory Due-Diligence','1. Research FDA requirements for mineral sunscreen products. 2. List all necessary registrations, labeling standards and testing protocols. 3. Identify timelines and costs for product listing and compliance. 4. Assign a regulatory owner and draft a compliance roadmap.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:57:42','2025-06-18 00:57:42'),(224,10,NULL,NULL,0,'competitive-forces','Secure Long-Term Raw Material Supply','1. List current shea butter and other key ingredient suppliers. 2. Request proposals for 12-month fixed-price supply contracts with volume tiers. 3. Compare quotes and negotiate minimum price protections. 4. Draft and sign supply agreements, ensuring exclusivity or first-refusal clauses.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:57:42','2025-06-18 00:57:42'),(225,10,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Launch Affiliate & Influencer Program','1. Define commission structure, performance metrics and contract terms. 2. Compile a target list of 20 relevant influencers and affiliate partners in skincare/mineral sunscreen niches. 3. Draft outreach email templates and NDAs. 4. Schedule introductory calls and finalize agreements.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:57:42','2025-06-18 00:57:42'),(226,10,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Recruit for US Expansion Roles','1. Create org chart for US launch team (e.g. marketing lead, regulatory manager). 2. Develop detailed job descriptions and key performance indicators. 3. Post roles on industry job boards and LinkedIn. 4. Screen resumes, conduct interviews and make offers within 30 days.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:57:42','2025-06-18 00:57:42'),(227,10,NULL,NULL,0,'general','Establish Weekly Management Review Meetings','1. Schedule a recurring 60-minute meeting every Monday with senior management. 2. Circulate an agenda template covering inventory, cash flow, production KPIs, CRM progress, US launch. 3. Assign a rotating minute-taker to record decisions and action items. 4. Distribute meeting minutes and action-tracking sheet within 24 hours of each meeting.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:57:42','2025-06-18 00:57:42'),(228,10,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Verify License Compliance for SPF Launch','1. Review expiry dates and conditions of TGA, AICIS and EPA licenses. 2. Confirm any additional registrations needed for US SPF product. 3. If expiry within 12 months, prepare renewal applications and supporting documentation. 4. Submit renewals by the end of the month and track approvals.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:57:42','2025-06-18 00:57:42'),(229,10,NULL,NULL,0,'tax','Tax Review & Pre-Sale Planning','1. Engage Grant-Lee & Co to review current tax positions and historical compliance. 2. Confirm all activity statements and tax returns are up to date. 3. Model tax liability scenarios under different sale structures. 4. Document recommendations and integrate them into the due-diligence pack.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:57:42','2025-06-18 00:57:42'),(230,11,NULL,NULL,0,'general','Develop Succession and Continuity Plan','1. Map all current roles, responsibilities and workflows performed by Alan Turner and Kate Turner; 2. Identify at least two internal candidates for each key role; 3. Create a development and handover schedule with training modules and timelines; 4. Draft a formal written plan, circulate to the board for review, and obtain sign-off; 5. Store the final plan in the corporate governance folder and review quarterly.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:59:40','2025-06-18 00:59:40'),(231,11,NULL,NULL,0,'tax','File Overdue BAS and Tax Returns','1. Collect ledger data and bank statements for all outstanding periods; 2. Engage Yearn & Co to prepare and reconcile all overdue activity statements (BAS); 3. Lodge all BAS with the ATO immediately; 4. Prepare and lodge the overdue company tax returns; 5. Confirm lodgment receipts and update the compliance register.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:59:40','2025-06-18 00:59:40'),(232,11,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Engage Bookkeeper and Implement Quarterly Financial Reviews','1. Define bookkeeping requirements and shortlist qualified candidates or firms; 2. Hire a bookkeeper and grant them secure access to accounting software; 3. Arrange an introductory meeting between the bookkeeper, Alan Turner and F Yearn; 4. Schedule quarterly financial review meetings in the calendar with agenda items (P&L, balance sheet, cash flow forecasts); 5. Distribute meeting minutes and action items promptly.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:59:40','2025-06-18 00:59:40'),(233,11,NULL,NULL,0,'competitive-forces','Conduct Supplier Cost Audit and Diversification','1. Compile current aluminium purchase volumes, costs and supplier terms; 2. Request quotes from at least three alternative local and regional suppliers; 3. Compare pricing, lead times, quality certifications and payment terms; 4. Negotiate with preferred new suppliers and secure trial orders; 5. Research aluminium price hedging instruments (e.g. futures contracts) and engage a financial advisor to set up a hedging strategy.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:59:40','2025-06-18 00:59:40'),(234,11,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Document Core Operational Processes','1. Identify the top five mission-critical processes (e.g. procurement, production scheduling, quality control); 2. Assign a process owner for each and map detailed step-by-step workflows; 3. Create standard operating procedure (SOP) documents with flowcharts; 4. Review drafts with frontline staff and refine; 5. Store finalized SOPs in a centralized digital folder and communicate