ory data fields and segmentation criteria (e.g. repeat vs new customers); 3. Conduct two training workshops for sales and marketing teams; 4. Set up automated CRM reports to track customer acquisition, retention and marketing ROI; 5. Review CRM usage monthly and refine processes.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:59:40','2025-06-18 00:59:40'),(239,11,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Plan E-commerce and Marketplaces Expansion','1. Extract sales, traffic and conversion data from the existing online store; 2. Set realistic growth targets for the next 30 days and next quarter; 3. Research and shortlist at least two third-party marketplaces (e.g. Amazon, eBay) and understand their fee structures; 4. Develop a rollout plan for listing 10–20 best-selling SKUs on new channels; 5. Allocate a test budget for targeted digital advertising and track performance daily.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:59:40','2025-06-18 00:59:40'),(240,11,NULL,NULL,0,'due-diligence','Compile Due Diligence Documentation','1. Gather all corporate governance records (ABN, ASIC filings, minutes of board meetings); 2. Collect executed lease agreements, debt and asset lease contracts; 3. Assemble supplier agreements, customer contracts and service level agreements; 4. Organize intellectual property and branding documentation; 5. Create a secure digital ‘data room’ folder structure and invite advisors to review.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:59:40','2025-06-18 00:59:40'),(241,11,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Legal and Licensing Compliance Check','1. Review current operations against any industry regulations or licensing requirements; 2. Confirm in writing that no additional licences are required; 3. Document any applicable regulations or voluntary standards adhered to; 4. Update a compliance register and circulate to the board; 5. Schedule an annual compliance review.',NULL,0,'low',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:59:40','2025-06-18 00:59:40'),(242,11,NULL,NULL,0,'diagnostic','Establish Business Health Diagnostic Dashboard','1. Identify top-level business metrics (financial: P&L, cash flow; HR: absenteeism, turnover; ops: WIP age, production output); 2. Select a dashboard tool (Excel or BI platform) and link data sources; 3. Build visual dashboards and test data accuracy; 4. Schedule a monthly management review meeting; 5. Update and refine dashboard based on feedback.',NULL,0,'low',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 00:59:40','2025-06-18 00:59:40'),(243,11,NULL,NULL,0,'general','Develop and Implement Succession and Continuity Plan','Brian sander should map all critical roles currently held by Alan Turner and Kate Turner, identify internal or external candidates to backfill those roles, draft a formal succession document with step-by-step responsibilities, review the plan with the board, set clear timelines for handover tasks, and schedule quarterly reviews to update the plan.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:21','2025-06-18 01:00:21'),(244,11,NULL,NULL,0,'tax','Bring All BAS and Tax Returns Up to Date','Brian sander should gather all sales, purchase, payroll and bank statements for the past year, appoint a temporary bookkeeper if required, engage Yearn & Co immediately to prepare and lodge overdue BAS statements and tax returns, calculate and pay outstanding liabilities including penalties, and obtain confirmation of lodgement receipts.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:21','2025-06-18 01:00:21'),(245,11,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Establish Quarterly Accounting Review Meetings','Brian sander should contact F Yearn at Yearn & Co to secure a recurring quarterly meeting schedule, define a standard reporting pack (P&L, Balance Sheet, Cash Flow, WIP and stock reports), invite key stakeholders (MD, CFO or bookkeeper), prepare analysis in advance, and set follow-up actions and owners after each meeting.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:21','2025-06-18 01:00:21'),(246,11,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Document Core Processes and Launch Monthly Operational Reporting','Brian sander should list the top five operational processes (order entry, production scheduling, quality control, inventory management, dispatch), assign process owners, create step-by-step process documentation templates, store them in a shared operations manual, develop a monthly operations report template (including KPIs like throughput, cycle time, scrap rate), and schedule a monthly review meeting with division heads.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:21','2025-06-18 01:00:21'),(247,11,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Create Formal HR Policies, Position Descriptions and Meeting Cadence','Brian sander should draft an HR policy and procedure manual covering recruitment, performance management, absenteeism, leave and exit processes, update or create position descriptions for all roles, implement a schedule of monthly team meetings within each division, and define an annual performance review calendar for all employees.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:21','2025-06-18 01:00:21'),(248,11,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Tighten Working Capital Controls on Stock and WIP','Brian sander should conduct a full inventory audit to identify stock above the minimum and WIP older than three days, set up reorder points and approval thresholds, configure alerts in the ERP or inventory system for excess stock or aging WIP, and assign a monthly reconciliation and review process with finance and operations teams.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:21','2025-06-18 01:00:21'),(249,11,NULL,NULL,0,'competitive-forces','Implement Cost-Control and Supplier Diversification Plan','Brian sander should document current aluminium and timber supplier contracts, research and shortlist at least three alternative domestic and international suppliers, issue RFQs with standardized cost and lead-time metrics, negotiate better terms or bulk-buy discounts, and evaluate raw-material hedging options through commodity forward contracts or supplier pricing agreements.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:21','2025-06-18 01:00:21'),(250,11,NULL,NULL,0,'due-diligence','Audit Lease and Debt Covenant Compliance','Brian sander should review the factory lease to note the next CPI rent review date (October 2025) and extension options, compile all debt agreements (NAB term loan, asset leases), confirm covenant requirements and repayment schedules, enter critical dates into a compliance calendar, and prepare a summary report for the board.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:21','2025-06-18 01:00:21'),(251,11,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Upgrade CRM System and Define Data-Driven Sales Process','Brian sander should evaluate the current CRM\'s gaps, research and demo at least two higher-functionality CRM platforms, migrate existing customer data with clean-up, establish customer segmentation criteria (new, repeat, lapsed, high-value), define a standard sales process template with stages and entry/exit criteria, train the sales team, and set weekly usage targets.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:21','2025-06-18 01:00:21'),(252,11,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Expand E-Commerce Channel and Onboard Third-Party Marketplaces','Brian sander should analyse current e-commerce analytics to identify top SKUs, select two relevant marketplaces (e.g., Amazon, eBay), register business accounts, integrate inventory and order management with the ERP system, create product listings with professional imagery and descriptions, launch an initial marketing campaign, and track monthly online revenue growth.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:21','2025-06-18 01:00:21'),(253,11,NULL,NULL,0,'due-diligence','Conduct Export Market Feasibility and Compliance Study','Brian sander should identify three target export markets, research regulatory requirements (customs, labeling, duties), estimate shipping and logistics costs via freight forwarders, calculate landed cost per unit, draft a simple business case comparing domestic vs export margins, and present findings to the leadership team for go/no-go decision.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:21','2025-06-18 01:00:21'),(254,11,NULL,NULL,0,'diagnostic','Build a KPI Dashboard for Monthly Board Reviews','Brian sander should list key diagnostics (financial P&L, cash flow, inventory turnover, WIP age, absenteeism, sales by channel), select a dashboard tool (e.g., Power BI, Tableau), configure data connections, design a visual dashboard template, test for accuracy, and schedule a monthly board meeting to review and assign action items.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:21','2025-06-18 01:00:21'),(255,11,NULL,NULL,0,'due-diligence','Develop and Implement Succession and Continuity Plan','1. Map all key tasks and responsibilities performed by Alan Turner and Kate Turner. 2. Identify at least two internal candidates for MD and payroll roles. 3. Document detailed job descriptions and handover timelines. 4. Draft a continuity policy outlining emergency protocols and delegation authorities. 5. Review plan with board and legal advisor, finalize and publish.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:35','2025-06-18 01:00:35'),(256,11,NULL,NULL,0,'tax','Catch Up and Lodge Overdue BAS and Tax Returns','1. Compile all financial records for the past 12 months. 2. Engage Yearn & Co to prepare and review outstanding activity statements. 3. Complete and lodge overdue BAS within 14 days. 4. Prepare and lodge prior-year tax returns within 30 days. 5. Confirm lodgement receipts and file all supporting documentation.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:35','2025-06-18 01:00:35'),(257,11,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Schedule Quarterly Financial Reviews with Accountant','1. Contact F Yearn at Yearn & Co to set standing appointments for the next four quarters. 2. Define agenda: P&L, balance sheet, cash flow forecast, budget variances. 3. Prepare financial pack one week before each meeting. 4. Assign action items and track completion in shared folder.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:35','2025-06-18 01:00:35'),(258,11,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Tighten Working Capital and Inventory Controls','1. Review current WIP and stock levels against minimum thresholds. 2. Define reorder points and safety stock for key materials. 3. Implement weekly inventory review meetings with procurement and production leads. 4. Update stock valuation and control report in ERP system.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:35','2025-06-18 01:00:35'),(259,11,NULL,NULL,0,'competitive-forces','Conduct Supplier Diversification and Aluminium Price Hedging','1. List current aluminium and component suppliers and contract terms. 2. Research 3 alternative suppliers (domestic and regional). 3. Request quotes and assess delivery reliability. 4. Negotiate trial contracts and payment terms. 5. Investigate hedging instruments (forward contracts or futures) with finance provider.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:35','2025-06-18 01:00:35'),(260,11,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Document Core Operational Processes','1. Select five high-impact processes: procurement, production scheduling, quality control, order fulfillment, dispatch. 2. Conduct workshops with process owners to map each step in flowcharts. 3. Draft standard operating procedures (SOPs) with roles, inputs, outputs and KPIs. 4. Circulate drafts for feedback, revise and finalize. 5. Store SOPs in centralized document repository.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:35','2025-06-18 01:00:35'),(261,11,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Establish Monthly Operational Reporting Cadence','1. Define key operational KPIs (uptime, on-time delivery, scrap rate, throughput). 2. Build dashboard in Excel or BI tool linking to production data. 3. Schedule a recurring monthly ops review meeting with MD and division heads. 4. Assign report preparation responsibilities. 5. Review and refine KPI set after first cycle.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:35','2025-06-18 01:00:35'),(262,11,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Audit and Upgrade Automation and Tech Tools','1. List all current systems (ERP, CRM, scheduling, accounting). 2. Rate each system for functionality, integration and user satisfaction. 3. Identify top three automation gaps (manual data entry, reporting delays, order tracking). 4. Research potential add-on modules or new solutions. 5. Develop pilot implementation plan for one automation upgrade within 30 days.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:35','2025-06-18 01:00:35'),(263,11,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Create and Publish HR Policy Manual','1. Gather industry-standard templates for recruitment, onboarding, performance management, leave and code of conduct. 2. Draft customized policies reflecting Greenside culture and legal requirements. 3. Review with legal advisor if necessary. 4. Format into a handbook and distribute digitally to all employees. 5. Schedule a policy-orientation session within 30 days.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:35','2025-06-18 01:00:35'),(264,11,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Implement Regular Team Meetings and Performance Reviews','1. Set weekly division-level meetings with fixed agendas (production updates, issues, targets). 2. Schedule quarterly all-management strategy sessions. 3. Create simple meeting templates and circulate in advance. 4. Develop a monthly 1:1 performance review calendar for all staff. 5. Train managers on conducting feedback conversations.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:35','2025-06-18 01:00:35'),(265,11,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Overhaul CRM and Sales Process','1. Define essential data fields (customer segment, purchase history, lead source). 2. Clean and import existing customer data into CRM. 3. Configure lead scoring rules and automated reminders. 4. Develop a structured sales pipeline with defined stages. 5. Train sales and service teams on new CRM workflows.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:35','2025-06-18 01:00:35'),(266,11,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Develop E-commerce Expansion Plan','1. Audit current online store for UX, SEO and mobile performance. 2. Analyze competitors and third-party marketplaces (eBay, Amazon). 3. Define a sales target increase (e.g., from 10% to 15%). 4. Draft a six-month action plan covering site enhancements, platform listings, promotions. 5. Assign responsibilities and set weekly progress check-ins.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:35','2025-06-18 01:00:35'),(267,11,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Implement Marketing ROI Tracking','1. List all active digital and offline marketing channels. 2. Install analytics tags (Google Analytics, Facebook Pixel) and UTM parameters. 3. Define key conversion events (quote requests, online orders). 4. Create a dashboard to track spend vs conversions by channel. 5. Review weekly and adjust budgets based on performance.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:35','2025-06-18 01:00:35'),(268,11,NULL,NULL,0,'general','Draft 3-Year Strategic Business Plan','1. Facilitate a half-day strategy workshop with senior leaders. 2. Define vision, mission and strategic objectives (export growth, digital sales). 3. Conduct SWOT incorporating raw-material risk and competition. 4. Outline key initiatives with owners, timelines and owners. 5. Circulate draft, gather feedback and finalize plan.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-18 01:00:35','2025-06-18 01:00:35'),(269,3,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Renew Expiring Licences','1. Review the licence expiry dates for manufacturing (12/07/2025) and safety (01/07/2025). 2. Immediately contact the relevant regulatory bodies to confirm renewal requirements and fees. 3. Complete and submit renewal applications at least 60 days before expiry. 4. Pay associated fees ($8,000 for manufacturing, $5,263 for safety) and confirm receipt of renewed licences. 5. File digital and physical copies of renewed licences in a central compliance folder.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-19 23:36:36','2025-06-19 23:36:36'),(270,3,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Establish Rolling Licence Renewal Calendar','1. Create a shared calendar (e.g., Google Calendar or Outlook) listing all licence types with expiry and renewal reminder dates. 2. Set automated reminders 90, 60, and 30 days before each licence expiry. 3. Assign a responsible owner (e.g., operations manager) to monitor upcoming renewals. 4. Document renewal steps and contacts in a standard operating procedure (SOP). 5. Train staff on how to update and use the calendar.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-19 23:36:36','2025-06-19 23:36:36'),(271,3,NULL,NULL,0,'tax','File Overdue Activity Statements','1. Review ATO portal to identify missing BAS lodgements. 2. Gather financial data and reconcile transactions for each outstanding period. 3. Complete and lodge overdue activity statements immediately. 4. Schedule fortnightly meetings with your bookkeeper to prevent future backlogs. 5. Set up calendar alerts for future BAS due dates and assign responsibility.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-19 23:36:36','2025-06-19 23:36:36'),(272,3,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Meet with Accountant Monthly and Improve Financial Reporting','1. Schedule monthly meetings with Forsyths (Bob Hope) instead of annually. 2. Prepare P&L, Balance Sheet, bank and inventory reports one week before each meeting. 3. Review cash flow forecasts, overdraft usage, credit card balances and owner injections. 4. Identify cost realignment opportunities and set debt reduction targets. 5. Document action items and track progress in a shared spreadsheet.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-19 23:36:36','2025-06-19 23:36:36'),(273,3,NULL,NULL,0,'general','Activate and Test Succession Plan','1. Review the existing succession plan document with key stakeholders. 2. Identify and appoint deputies for critical owner functions (general management, financial oversight). 3. Conduct a simulation exercise: owner Peter Spinda steps aside for one full day; deputy performs his duties. 4. Document gaps and update training materials. 5. Schedule quarterly simulation exercises until full coverage is proven.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-19 23:36:36','2025-06-19 23:36:36'),(274,3,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Integrate and Optimize CRM with ERP','1. Audit current CRM (Infusionsoft) and ERP (Xero) data fields to identify gaps. 2. Work with your IT provider to enable data sync between CRM and ERP. 3. Import full customer history, segmentation and contract data into CRM. 4. Train sales and customer service teams on using the integrated system for lead tracking and retention dashboards. 5. Set up weekly reports to monitor churn risk and top-customer engagement.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-19 23:36:36','2025-06-19 23:36:36'),(275,3,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Implement Sales and Marketing ROI Tracking','1. Document all current sales and marketing channels and annual budgets ($10K–$25K digital, $1K–$10K offline). 2. For each channel, define measurable KPIs (leads generated, conversion rate, revenue). 3. Set up UTM tracking and lead source tagging in Infusionsoft. 4. Create a dashboard to report on spend vs revenue for each campaign. 5. Review results bi-weekly and reallocate budget to top-performing channels.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-19 23:36:36','2025-06-19 23:36:36'),(276,3,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Rationalise WIP and Inventory Levels','1. Extract WIP and stock reports from ERP: identify items over 90 days in WIP and slow-moving inventory. 2. Prioritise WIP worth $856K for completion or cancellation within 30 days. 3. Set minimum and maximum stock levels based on the lowest manageable stock of $125K. 4. Negotiate extended payment terms with top suppliers to ease cash flow. 5. Adjust reorder points in ERP and communicate changes to purchasing team.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-19 23:36:36','2025-06-19 23:36:36'),(277,3,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Formalise Performance Reviews and KPIs','1. Develop standard 1:1 performance review templates for all staff. 2. Schedule the first round of reviews within 30 days for all permanent and key employees. 3. Define clear KPIs linked to productivity (busy rating target 85%), quality and attendance metrics. 4. Train supervisors (e.g., Bob the supervisor) on conducting reviews and documenting outcomes. 5. Set up a quarterly cycle for ongoing reviews and link goals to training plans.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-19 23:36:36','2025-06-19 23:36:36'),(278,3,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Conduct Process Documentation Audit','1. Inventory all documented processes and procedures, noting last review dates (unknown). 2. Assign process owners for each major function (manufacturing, sales, finance). 3. Schedule review meetings to update SOPs with current best practices. 4. Rate process effectiveness and identify top three areas for immediate improvement. 5. Implement a version-control system and schedule bi-annual reviews.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-19 23:36:36','2025-06-19 23:36:36'),(279,3,NULL,NULL,0,'due-diligence','Compile Due Diligence Pack for Sale Readiness','1. Gather corporate documents: ABNs, shareholder and director registers, licences, property leases, encumbrances and IP listings. 2. Prepare a debt schedule including car loans and equipment finance details. 3. Collate financial statements, BAS lodgements and tax returns for the past 3 years. 4. Summarise key operational metrics (utilisation rates, WIP, top customers). 5. Store all documents in a secure data room and create an index for buyer reference.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-19 23:36:36','2025-06-19 23:36:36'),(280,3,NULL,NULL,0,'competitive-forces','Review Competitive Threats and Opportunities','1. List direct competitors (Manuf R Us, Clins Manuf) with their strengths, weaknesses and pricing. 2. Research emerging overseas entrants and material innovations. 3. Identify 2–3 partnerships or product innovations to counter threats. 4. Develop an action plan to leverage your sustainable advantage (manufacturing expertise). 5. Present findings in a management meeting and assign owners to next steps.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-19 23:36:36','2025-06-19 23:36:36'),(281,13,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Schedule Monthly Strategy Sessions with Accountant','1. Contact Bob Hope at Forsyths to propose a recurring monthly meeting. 2. Block a 90-minute slot each month in your calendar. 3. Prepare and circulate agenda one week before each session, including cash-flow projections, tax planning, and exit strategies. 4. Document action items and track completion in a shared drive.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-04 04:04:30','2025-07-04 04:04:30'),(282,13,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Renegotiate Lease Agreements to Reduce Cash Outflows','1. Gather all lease contracts for the 10 leased properties. 2. Engage legal counsel specialized in commercial real estate. 3. Prepare a financial impact analysis showing current vs. proposed rent terms. 4. Reach out to each landlord to request meetings. 5. Propose staggered rent relief or extended terms to lower annual payments. 6. Document any letters of intent and draft amendment agreements.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-04 04:04:30','2025-07-04 04:04:30'),(283,13,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Develop Cash-Flow Forecast Including Lease Restructuring','1. Use last 12 months of P&L, balance sheet, and bank statements. 2. Model current lease liabilities (A$2.52M over 3 years). 3. Incorporate proposed renegotiated terms. 4. Forecast monthly cash flows for the next 12 months. 5. Identify any potential shortfalls and funding sources. 6. Share the forecast with your accountant for review.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-04 04:04:30','2025-07-04 04:04:30'),(284,13,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Engage Business-Process Consultant for Lean Mapping','1. Research and shortlist at least three process-reengineering firms. 2. Issue an RFP outlining objectives: workflow mapping, waste identification, efficiency targets. 3. Evaluate proposals and select consultant by week 2. 4. Schedule on-site workshops to map key manufacturing and back-office processes. 5. Review deliverables and implement quick-win improvements within 30 days.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-04 04:04:30','2025-07-04 04:04:30'),(285,13,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','CRM Optimization and Automation Plan','1. Audit current CRM usage and data quality. 2. Define key sales metrics (lead response time, conversion rate). 3. Configure automated follow-up email sequences for new leads. 4. Integrate CRM with sales-analytics dashboard. 5. Train sales team on updated workflows. 6. Monitor CRM KPIs weekly and adjust settings.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-04 04:04:30','2025-07-04 04:04:30'),(286,13,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Conduct Price Review and Update Catalog','1. Collect competitor pricing data for comparable roofing products. 2. Calculate cost plus margin targets against current pricing. 3. Identify products with outdated pricing (last updated 6 months ago). 4. Update price list in ERP/CRM and on any external quotations. 5. Communicate new prices to sales team and key customers.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-04 04:04:30','2025-07-04 04:04:30'),(287,13,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Create Digital Sales Channel Roadmap','1. Define objectives for e-commerce site and marketplace presence. 2. Identify platform options (Shopify, Amazon, eBay). 3. Map out integration requirements with inventory system. 4. Draft project timeline with milestones: platform selection, design, content upload, testing, launch. 5. Assign internal owner and schedule weekly check-ins.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-04 04:04:30','2025-07-04 04:04:30'),(288,13,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Plan Team-Building and Leadership Coaching Program','1. Survey staff to identify engagement gaps. 2. Research reputable leadership coaches and team-building facilitators. 3. Schedule a full-day workshop in weeks 2–3. 4. Develop follow-up plan with monthly small-group activities. 5. Measure staff morale and cohesion before and after interventions.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-04 04:04:30','2025-07-04 04:04:30'),(289,13,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Evaluate ERP and Inventory-Management Solutions','1. List functional requirements: real-time stock levels, reorder alerts, integration with sales channels. 2. Demo at least three ERP vendors. 3. Score each solution against requirements and total cost of ownership. 4. Prepare a recommendation report. 5. Plan pilot implementation for high-impact location.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-04 04:04:30','2025-07-04 04:04:30'),(290,13,NULL,NULL,0,'due-diligence','Compile Exit-Ready Due-Diligence Package','1. Gather audited financial statements for past 3 years. 2. Document EBITDA reconciliation and key margin drivers. 3. Prepare a summary of operations improvements (process mapping, tech integration). 4. Collate customer retention metrics and CRM performance data. 5. Assemble legal, property, and regulatory compliance records. 6. Store the package on a secure data room.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-04 04:04:30','2025-07-04 04:04:30'),(291,13,NULL,NULL,0,'competitive-forces','Perform Competitive Analysis for Digital Market Entry','1. Identify top 5 roofing product sellers on target e-commerce platforms. 2. Analyze their pricing, promotions, and customer reviews. 3. Benchmark their site UX and fulfillment options. 4. Prepare SWOT summary and identify differentiation opportunities. 5. Integrate findings into the digital sales channel roadmap.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-04 04:04:30','2025-07-04 04:04:30'),(292,13,NULL,NULL,0,'tax','Review and Update Tax Projections for Exit Planning','1. Confirm all business tax returns and activity statements are lodged. 2. Work with Forsyths to model capital gains tax implications of sale. 3. Identify potential concessions (small business CGT, rollover relief). 4. Document recommendations and action steps. 5. File any necessary forms within due-dates.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-04 04:04:30','2025-07-04 04:04:30'),(293,13,NULL,NULL,0,'diagnostic','Diagnostic Audit of Technology Sync and Integration Gaps','1. List all core systems: accounting, CRM, inventory, manufacturing controls. 2. Map current data flows and sync points. 3. Identify manual workarounds and data-lag issues. 4. Quantify time spent on manual reconciliations. 5. Propose prioritized integration solutions.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-04 04:04:30','2025-07-04 04:04:30'),(294,3,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Renew Manufacturing Licence and Safety Certificates','1. Gather existing licence documents (manufacturing and safety).\n2. Contact the licensing authority for renewal forms.\n3. Complete and submit renewal applications before expiry dates (20/06/2025 & 01/06/2025).\n4. Pay fees $8000 and $5263.\n5. Upload confirmation to central compliance folder.\n6. Schedule reminder 60 days before next expiry.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-07 01:21:29','2025-07-07 01:21:29'),(295,3,NULL,NULL,0,'tax','Update ATO Activity Statements','1. Collect list of outstanding BAS and GLS from bookkeeper.\n2. Reconcile sales and purchase data for each period.\n3. Submit all overdue activity statements via the ATO portal.\n4. Record lodgment receipt numbers and file in tax records.\n5. Set up calendar reminders for future monthly lodgments.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-07 01:21:29','2025-07-07 01:21:29'),(296,3,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Schedule Monthly Financial Review Meetings','1. Contact Forsyths to propose shifting from annual to monthly reviews.\n2. Agree on meeting dates and circulate invites to finance team and owners.\n3. Prepare P&L, balance sheet, cash-flow and WIP reports one week in advance.\n4. Distribute reports to attendees prior to each meeting.\n5. Document decisions and action items, assign owners and follow up.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-07 01:21:29','2025-07-07 01:21:29'),(297,3,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Implement Cost Control and Margin Improvement Initiatives','1. Identify top three expense categories (contractors, casual staff, permanent staff).\n2. Analyze spend trends and negotiate rate reductions with contractors.\n3. Optimize staffing rosters to minimize overtime and casual headcount.\n4. Establish monthly cost-vs-budget targets for each category.\n5. Review actuals in monthly financial meetings and report savings.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-07 01:21:29','2025-07-07 01:21:29'),(298,3,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Document and Activate Succession Plan','1. Retrieve existing succession plan and review current gaps.\n2. List critical owner duties and map required competencies.\n3. Identify potential internal successors and assign mentors.\n4. Create a 30-day cross-training schedule for each duty.\n5. Conduct a handover simulation and document outcomes.\n6. Update the plan based on feedback and set quarterly reviews.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-07 01:21:29','2025-07-07 01:21:29'),(299,3,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Create Delegation and Decision-Making Framework','1. Inventory all decisions currently made by the owner.\n2. Define a decision-rights matrix by role.\n3. Assign each decision to the appropriate manager or team.\n4. Communicate the new framework to all stakeholders.\n5. Monitor adherence and refine the framework after 30 days.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-07 01:21:29','2025-07-07 01:21:29'),(300,3,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Develop Customer Diversification Plan','1. Export revenue data from CRM and calculate concentration ratios.\n2. Identify three new target industries or regions.\n3. Set weekly prospecting goals (e.g., 3 new leads per week).\n4. Create outreach templates and train sales on messaging.\n5. Track prospecting activity and conversion in CRM weekly.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-07 01:21:29','2025-07-07 01:21:29'),(301,3,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Launch Targeted Digital Marketing Campaign','1. Audit current website and social media presence.\n2. Define campaign objectives (lead generation, brand awareness) and KPIs.\n3. Select channels (Google Ads, LinkedIn Ads) and allocate budget.\n4. Develop ad copy, design creatives and set up tracking.\n5. Launch campaign, monitor performance weekly and optimize.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-07 01:21:29','2025-07-07 01:21:29'),(302,3,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Design Service/Maintenance Contract Offering','1. List product lines and common maintenance needs.\n2. Draft standard service contract templates with clear terms.\n3. Price packages to achieve healthy margins.\n4. Train sales/customer service teams on upsell scripts.\n5. Pilot offering with top 20 clients and gather feedback.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-07 01:21:29','2025-07-07 01:21:29'),(303,3,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Establish Performance Review Process','1. Draft a performance-review template with KPIs, competencies and rating scales.\n2. Define review frequency (e.g., quarterly) and schedule 1:1s.\n3. Train managers on conducting objective, constructive reviews.\n4. Roll out first review cycle, collect signed forms and feedback.\n5. Refine process based on participant feedback for next cycle.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-07 01:21:29','2025-07-07 01:21:29'),(304,3,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Document and Update All Job Descriptions','1. Gather current role summaries from each department head.\n2. Draft detailed job description templates (responsibilities, skills, KPIs).\n3. Review drafts with managers and refine content.\n4. Publish final JDs in the employee handbook and HR system.\n5. Communicate updates to staff and file signed copies.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-07 01:21:29','2025-07-07 01:21:29'),(305,3,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Plan Staff Engagement and Culture-Building Activity','1. Conduct an anonymous staff survey to identify morale drivers.\n2. Select one targeted team-building workshop or offsite.\n3. Book venue, facilitator and set date within 30 days.\n4. Distribute event details and objectives to all employees.\n5. Collect post-event feedback and develop follow-up actions.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-07 01:21:29','2025-07-07 01:21:29'),(306,3,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Assess and Improve ERP System Effectiveness','1. Collect user feedback on ERP pain points and missing features.\n2. Document key business processes requiring optimization.\n3. Prioritize top three quick-win configuration changes.\n4. Engage IT support or ven