 dashboard tool (e.g., Power BI, Google Data Studio). 3. Connect data sources and build visual reports. 4. Train senior team on interpreting and acting on insights.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-28 03:43:44','2025-07-28 03:43:44'),(371,3,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Renew and Update All Operating Licenses','1. Pull the licence register and identify expiry dates for the manufacturing, roofing, and safety licences. 2. Gather renewal documentation (e.g., compliance certificates, insurance proofs). 3. Contact each licensing body to confirm submission requirements and fees. 4. Complete and submit renewal applications at least 30 days before expiry. 5. Record payment confirmations and update the compliance calendar.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-19 23:46:04','2025-08-19 23:46:04'),(372,3,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Conduct a Full Financial and Cost-Control Review','1. Meet with your accountant to generate a detailed P&L, balance sheet, and cash-flow statement for the last 12 months. 2. Identify the top three expense lines (contractors, casual staff, permanent staff). 3. Set cost-reduction targets (e.g., 10% reduction in contractor spend) and assign responsibility. 4. Implement weekly expense tracking in your accounting software. 5. Report progress at weekly leadership huddles.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-19 23:46:04','2025-08-19 23:46:04'),(373,3,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Optimize Working Capital and Inventory Levels','1. Extract stock, WIP, debtors, and creditors data from Xero. 2. Compare current stock ($500K) against minimum required ($125K) and minimum saleable stock ($268K). 3. Create action plan to reduce slow-moving stock by offering discounts or returning excess to suppliers. 4. Set target WIP reduction of 20% by accelerating billing cycles. 5. Assign a weekly review owner and track improvements in a shared dashboard.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-19 23:46:04','2025-08-19 23:46:04'),(374,3,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Develop a Structured 90-Day Sales & Marketing Plan','1. Convene a workshop with sales, marketing, and operations to define target customer segments. 2. Allocate digital marketing budget ($10–25K) across channels (e.g., Google Ads, LinkedIn). 3. Create a weekly calendar with specific campaigns, content calendar, and lead-generation goals. 4. Define ROI metrics (cost per lead, conversion rate, customer acquisition cost). 5. Assign campaign owners and set bi-weekly review meetings to monitor performance.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-19 23:46:04','2025-08-19 23:46:04'),(375,3,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Implement and Clean Up Your CRM for ROI Tracking','1. Audit the Infusionsoft CRM for missing or duplicate records. 2. Standardize customer seg­mentation fields (existing, lapsed, prospects). 3. Build custom fields to capture source, campaign, and spend. 4. Train sales staff on data entry standards and workflows. 5. Run an initial report on lead conversion rates and present findings in the next sales meeting.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-19 23:46:04','2025-08-19 23:46:04'),(376,3,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Activate Succession Planning Framework','1. Review existing succession plan documents to identify gaps. 2. List critical owner-dependent roles and potential internal successors. 3. Draft individual development plans (training, mentoring, job-shadows) for each successor. 4. Schedule weekly 1:1 coaching sessions between owners and successors. 5. Track progress in a shared succession-plan tracker and report monthly to the board.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-19 23:46:04','2025-08-19 23:46:04'),(377,3,NULL,NULL,0,'general','Launch Weekly Leadership Team Meetings with Clear Agendas','1. Set a recurring weekly 60-minute meeting with CEO, GM, and division heads. 2. Circulate an agenda 24 hours before (financials, sales pipeline, operations issues). 3. Use a standard action/tasking sheet to record decisions and owners. 4. Distribute meeting minutes within 24 hours, highlighting due dates. 5. Monitor completion of action items at the start of each meeting.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-19 23:46:04','2025-08-19 23:46:04'),(378,3,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Roll Out Performance Reviews and Team-Building Activities','1. Draft a simple performance-review template covering goals, competencies, and development areas. 2. Schedule 30-minute 1:1 meetings for all staff (full-time, part-time, contractors) over the next two weeks. 3. Provide training for managers on giving feedback using the template. 4. Organize a half-day team-building workshop to address culture and cohesion issues. 5. Gather feedback post-workshop and adjust the ongoing HR calendar.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-19 23:46:04','2025-08-19 23:46:04'),(379,3,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Map and Re-Engineer Key Production Processes','1. Identify top three manufacturing processes causing delays or WIP overhang. 2. Facilitate a process-mapping session with floor supervisors and key operators. 3. Highlight bottlenecks and brainstorm automation or streamlining opportunities. 4. Engage IT support to scope simple automation tools (e.g., barcode scanning, digital job cards). 5. Pilot one process change on a single production line and measure throughput improvements.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-19 23:46:04','2025-08-19 23:46:04'),(380,3,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Renegotiate Supplier Terms to Protect Margins','1. List the top five suppliers by spend and current pricing terms. 2. Prepare a margin-impact analysis to understand target cost reductions (e.g., 5%). 3. Request meetings with each supplier to discuss volume discounts, extended payment terms, or rebates. 4. Draft revised contract templates reflecting new terms and SLAs. 5. Finalize and sign off updated agreements, then update the supplier management tracker.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-19 23:46:04','2025-08-19 23:46:04'),(381,3,NULL,NULL,0,'competitive-forces','Update Competitive Analysis and Pricing Strategy','1. Gather updated data on your four main direct competitors (size, price, strengths, weaknesses). 2. Conduct a pricing benchmark to compare your product margins against industry standards. 3. Identify one product line to reposition on price or value-added features. 4. Draft a competitive-response plan (e.g., bundle services, introduce premium option). 5. Present recommendations to the leadership team for approval and rapid implementation.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-19 23:46:04','2025-08-19 23:46:04'),(382,3,NULL,NULL,0,'tax','Meet with Your Accountant for Tax and Debt-Reduction Strategy','1. Schedule a meeting with Bob from Forsyths within the next two weeks. 2. Prepare a summary of current debts (car loans, equipment finance) and interest rates. 3. Discuss opportunities to restructure or refinance for lower repayments. 4. Review upcoming tax liabilities and potential prepayments or deductions. 5. Agree on a quarterly meeting cadence to monitor progress on debt reduction and tax planning.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-19 23:46:04','2025-08-19 23:46:04'),(383,16,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Renew and Comply with Manufacturing Licence','1. Retrieve current licence documents and expiry notices. 2. Review all licence conditions and identify missing compliance items. 3. Prepare and assemble renewal application, including updated insurance certificates and safety audits. 4. Submit application and pay $8,000 renewal fee to the regulator. 5. Obtain and file renewed licence certificate. 6. Create a calendar reminder 90 days before expiry for future renewals.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-20 10:37:58','2025-08-20 10:37:58'),(384,16,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Implement Weekly Cash-flow Review with Accountant','1. Schedule a 60-minute meeting every Monday morning with Forsyths accountant. 2. Share updated bank statements, P&L and balance sheet reports 24 hours before each meeting. 3. Review overdraft, credit card balances and owner injections. 4. Identify top three cash outflows and propose cost controls. 5. Document action items and assign owners for follow-up.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-20 10:37:58','2025-08-20 10:37:58'),(385,16,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Conduct Detailed Cost and Pricing Analysis','1. Extract direct and indirect cost data from last 12 months. 2. Benchmark material, labour and overhead rates against three competitors. 3. Identify products with margin below 15%. 4. Propose revised price list reflecting cost increases and target margin of 20%. 5. Present recommendations to owner and update ERP pricing tables.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-20 10:37:58','2025-08-20 10:37:58'),(386,16,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Optimize Inventory and WIP Levels','1. Pull current stock and WIP valuations. 2. Calculate reorder points based on lowest manage stock of $125,000. 3. Set minimum and maximum inventory levels in the ERP system. 4. Implement forward-order scheduling to reduce WIP over three days. 5. Fast-track invoicing for completed jobs and follow up on outstanding receivables.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-20 10:37:58','2025-08-20 10:37:58'),(387,16,NULL,NULL,0,'general','Document and Delegate Owner-Critical Processes','1. Identify five key processes where owner is sole decision-maker (e.g., vendor approval, quality sign-off). 2. Map each process step-by-step and assign a responsible team member. 3. Create standard operating procedure (SOP) documents and store centrally. 4. Train delegates on each SOP and sign off in writing. 5. Review delegation effectiveness after two weeks.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-20 10:37:58','2025-08-20 10:37:58'),(388,16,NULL,NULL,0,'general','Schedule Recurring Monthly Strategic Review Meetings','1. Draft a standing agenda template covering financials, operations, HR and sales updates. 2. Send calendar invites to all directors and senior managers for the 1st Tuesday of each month. 3. Distribute pre-reading packs (P&L, KPI dashboard, action register) three days prior. 4. Capture minutes, action items and assign deadlines. 5. Circulate minutes within 48 hours.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-20 10:37:58','2025-08-20 10:37:58'),(389,16,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Develop Recruitment Plan and Job Descriptions','1. List all vacant and critical roles (skilled production staff, quality manager). 2. Draft detailed job descriptions with responsibilities, qualifications and KPIs. 3. Post adverts on industry job boards and LinkedIn. 4. Set up an application screening matrix. 5. Schedule interviews and target offer acceptance within 30 days.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-20 10:37:58','2025-08-20 10:37:58'),(390,16,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Implement Quarterly Performance Review Process','1. Design a simple performance review template covering objectives, competencies and development needs. 2. Schedule review meetings for all permanent and part-time staff within the next 30 days. 3. Train managers on giving constructive feedback. 4. Collect signed review documents and file in HR system. 5. Set next review date in each employee’s calendar.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-20 10:37:58','2025-08-20 10:37:58'),(391,16,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Audit CRM Usage and Train Team','1. Export CRM usage logs to identify gaps in data entry. 2. Create a standard data capture checklist for new leads and customers. 3. Hold a 2-hour training session for sales and admin teams on CRM best practices. 4. Assign a CRM champion to monitor data quality weekly. 5. Report CRM adoption metrics in monthly board meeting.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-20 10:37:58','2025-08-20 10:37:58'),(392,16,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Design and Deploy Structured Sales Process','1. Map sales stages (lead, qualification, proposal, negotiation, close) and decision-maker roles. 2. Integrate these stages into the CRM pipeline. 3. Create email and call scripts for each stage. 4. Train sales team on the new process in a 1-day workshop. 5. Track pipeline conversion rates weekly and adjust scripts as needed.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-20 10:37:58','2025-08-20 10:37:58'),(393,16,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Launch Marketing Test Campaigns with ROI Tracking','1. Allocate a dedicated $5,000 digital budget to two channels (e.g., LinkedIn ads, Google Ads). 2. Define KPIs (click-through rate, cost per lead, conversion rate). 3. Set up tracking URLs and dashboards in Google Analytics. 4. Run each campaign for 14 days. 5. Analyze results and adjust budget allocation based on cost per acquisition.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-20 10:37:58','2025-08-20 10:37:58'),(394,16,NULL,NULL,0,'due-diligence','Compile Compliance and Due Diligence File','1. Gather all regulatory documents: licence certificates, building code compliance, supplier and customer contracts. 2. Scan and organize files in a secure cloud folder structured by category. 3. List any missing or expiring items with renewal dates. 4. Assign an owner to monitor and update the folder monthly. 5. Verify completeness with a due-diligence checklist.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-20 10:37:58','2025-08-20 10:37:58'),(395,3,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Renew Licences and Ensure Regulatory Compliance','1. Gather all current licence documents (roofers, manufacturing, safety). 2. Complete renewal applications: roofers licence by 12/09/2024 and manufacturing licence by 12/06/2025. 3. Prepare payment of fees. 4. Submit to relevant Building Industry Authority. 5. Document approval and update compliance calendar for next review.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-21 02:30:52','2025-08-21 02:30:52'),(396,3,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Implement Weekly Financial Review Meetings','1. Schedule recurring weekly 60-minute meetings with accountant and owner. 2. Prepare P&L, balance sheet, cash-flow and WIP reports in Xero one day before each meeting. 3. Discuss variances, identify cost overruns (contractors, staff) and agree on corrective actions. 4. Assign responsibilities and track action items in a shared document.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-21 02:30:52','2025-08-21 02:30:52'),(397,3,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Reduce Cash-flow Pressure via Working Capital Optimisation','1. Run a stock-ageing report and identify SKUs above the minimum safe level. 2. Develop a plan to liquidate or return obsolete stock. 3. Generate debtor ageing report, segment top 10 slow-paying customers. 4. Issue payment reminders and negotiate payment plans. 5. Approach top 5 suppliers to request extended credit terms.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-21 02:30:52','2025-08-21 02:30:52'),(398,3,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Map and Streamline Production Processes to Reduce WIP','1. Assemble a cross-functional team including production supervisor, key operators and ERP specialist. 2. Document current end-to-end production workflow in a process map. 3. Identify bottlenecks and steps that exceed three-day WIP. 4. Define target WIP reduction metrics. 5. Implement lean practices: daily stand-up to review progress, kaizen suggestions and continuous improvement tracking.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-21 02:30:52','2025-08-21 02:30:52'),(399,3,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Integrate ERP, CRM and Accounting Systems','1. List all data flows between Xero, Infusionsoft and ERP. 2. Engage IT support or a systems integrator to draft an integration plan. 3. Validate mapping of customer, order and inventory data. 4. Test automated sync in a sandbox environment. 5. Deploy to production and train users on new workflows.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-21 02:30:52','2025-08-21 02:30:52'),(400,3,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Define and Update Position Descriptions','1. Collect existing job descriptions for all staff. 2. Conduct one-on-one meetings with each employee to clarify duties and skills. 3. Draft updated position descriptions covering roles, responsibilities, KPIs and reporting lines. 4. Circulate for review by HR lead and department heads. 5. Finalise and store in a central HR repository.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-21 02:30:52','2025-08-21 02:30:52'),(401,3,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Launch Performance Review and Feedback Process','1. Design a simple quarterly performance review template covering objectives, strengths, development needs. 2. Schedule half-hour review sessions with each staff member within 30 days. 3. Train managers on delivering constructive feedback. 4. Document outcomes and agree on individual development plans. 5. Track completion and follow up on action items monthly.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-21 02:30:52','2025-08-21 02:30:52'),(402,3,NULL,NULL,0,'general','Develop and Begin Succession Plan Implementation','1. Identify critical owner roles and potential internal successors. 2. Assign mentoring and cross-training activities over the next month. 3. Draft a contingency plan for owner absence (illness or departure). 4. Secure board approval for the plan and assign accountability. 5. Review progress weekly in management meeting.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-21 02:30:52','2025-08-21 02:30:52'),(403,3,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Establish a Proactive Sales Process with CRM','1. Document the current informal sales steps from lead to order. 2. Define a formal sales funnel with stages (lead, qualified, proposal, close). 3. Configure CRM to capture prospects, activities and deal values. 4. Train sales staff on data entry and pipeline management. 5. Set weekly KPI dashboard to track conversion rates and deal velocity.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-21 02:30:52','2025-08-21 02:30:52'),(404,3,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Diversify Customer Base to Reduce Concentration Risk','1. Analyze revenue by customer and identify those above 5% of total. 2. Set a target to reduce top 3 reliance from 52% to below 40%. 3. Generate a prospect list in under-served industries. 4. Assign outbound calls or email campaigns to sales reps. 5. Track new customer wins and monthly revenue contribution.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-21 02:30:52','2025-08-21 02:30:52'),(405,3,NULL,NULL,0,'competitive-forces','Conduct Competitor Pricing and Product Benchmarking','1. List main direct competitors and their public pricing. 2. Order sample products or request quotes for comparable items. 3. Document features, lead times and service offerings. 4. Compare margins and identify pricing gaps. 5. Present findings to management and adjust pricing strategy accordingly.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-21 02:30:52','2025-08-21 02:30:52'),(406,3,NULL,NULL,0,'general','Schedule Monthly Board and Strategic Review Meetings','1. Prepare a board meeting calendar for the next 6 months. 2. Draft a standard agenda covering financial performance, operations, HR and sales updates. 3. Distribute pre-reads one week in advance. 4. Assign action-item tracking to board secretary. 5. Convene the first meeting within 30 days to review strategic goals.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-21 02:30:52','2025-08-21 02:30:52'),(407,3,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Review Contractor, Casual and Permanent Staff Costs','1. Extract payroll and contractor spend reports for the last 12 months. 2. Identify top 3 cost drivers and utilization metrics. 3. Assess each role for potential insourcing or reduced hours. 4. Propose cost reduction targets and restructure options. 5. Present recommendations to owner and HR for implementation.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-21 02:30:52','2025-08-21 02:30:52'),(408,3,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Explore Alternative Financing Solutions','1. Research invoice financing, equipment leasing and working capital loans. 2. Shortlist at least two lenders or fintech platforms. 3. Prepare financial summaries and credit history to submit. 4. Request proposals and compare fees, rates and covenants. 5. Select a solution and initiate application before month end.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-21 02:30:52','2025-08-21 02:30:52'),(409,3,NULL,NULL,0,'tax','Prepare for Upcoming Tax and BAS Obligations','1. Confirm lodging dates for BAS and activity statements. 2. Reconcile payroll, GST and PAYG withholding with external bookkeeper. 3. Ensure all invoices and expenses are coded in Xero. 4. Validate prior year returns and check for outstanding obligations. 5. Submit any pending lodgements and calendar next year’s deadlines.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-21 02:30:52','2025-08-21 02:30:52'),(410,17,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Engage a qualified bookkeeper','Contact at least three bookkeeping firms within the next week, evaluate their services and fees, and appoint a bookkeeper by day 14. Provide the bookkeeper with access to bank and accounting data and establish a weekly catch-up call to review transactions.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 22:48:32','2025-08-26 22:48:32'),(411,17,NULL,NULL,0,'tax','Bring all outstanding Activity Statements up to date','Gather bank statements and sales records for the past 12 months, provide them to the bookkeeper and accountant, prepare and lodge outstanding BAS/IAS within 21 days, then set up a calendar reminder for monthly lodgements.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 22:48:32','2025-08-26 22:48:32'),(412,17,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Implement cloud accounting and inventory system','Research two cloud accounting packages (e.g., Xero, QuickBooks) and two inventory management platforms (e.g., Dear Systems, Cin7) by day 7. Run a 14-day free trial of each, evaluate integration options, select preferred tools by day 21, and begin data migration by day 30.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 22:48:32','2025-08-26 22:48:32'),(413,17,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Institute monthly P&L and cash-flow reviews','With the new bookkeeper, design P&L and cash-flow templates in the chosen accounting system. Schedule a recurring first-of-month meeting with Stacey and the accountant to review performance, note variances and record action items.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 22:48:32','2025-08-26 22:48:32'),(414,17,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Document core business processes and SOPs','List the 5 most critical workflows (e.g., order processing, stock reconciliation, payroll). For each, interview the responsible staff, map steps in a simple flowchart, and publish SOPs in a shared drive by day 30.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 22:48:32','2025-08-26 22:48:32'),(415,17,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Assign roles and develop organisational chart','Draft a one-page organisational chart showing current staff and reporting lines. Identify at least two key tasks to delegate from Stacey to staff, hold a staff meeting to communicate changes, and update job descriptions accordingly.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 22:48:32','2025-08-26 22:48:32'),(416,17,NULL,NULL,0,'due-diligence','Create a basic succession and continuity plan','Identify potential internal or external stand-ins for Stacey’s roles, document step-by-step emergency contacts and responsibilities, and formalise a 2-page continuity plan that can be activated if Stacey is unavailable.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 22:48:32','2025-08-26 22:48:32'),(417,17,NULL,NULL,0,'general','Schedule regular management and team meetings','Set up a recurring monthly management meeting and weekly team huddle with clear agendas (financials, operations, sales). Distribute meeting minutes and action logs within 24 hours after each meeting.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 22:48:32','2025-08-26 22:48:32'),(418,17,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Engage legal counsel to resolve compliance gaps','Within 7 days, shortlist three commercial law firms, request engagement proposals outlining fees and timelines, appoint counsel by day 14, and schedule an initial compliance audit to assess licences, insurance and any regulatory exposures.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 22:48:32','2025-08-26 22:48:32'),(419,17,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Compile and maintain a compliance register','Work with legal counsel to list all required permits, licences and regulatory obligations (even if currently none). Record renewal dates, responsible person and documentation location in a spreadsheet accessible to management.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 22:48:32','2025-08-26 22:48:32'),(420,17,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Negotiate equipment loan restructuring','Contact the lender within 5 days to request updated repayment schedule options. Prepare cash-flow forecasts with the bookkeeper to support your case, propose reduced repayments or extended term, and finalize terms by day 30.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 22:48:32','2025-08-26 22:48:32'),(421,17,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Reduce reliance on overdraft facility','Meet with your bank relationship manager to explore alternative working-capital solutions (invoice finance, line of credit). Obtain written proposals, compare costs, and decide on a replacement facility by the end of the month.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 22:48:32','2025-08-26 22:48:32'),(422,17,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Develop a basic CRM and customer re-engagement plan','Select a simple CRM tool (e.g., HubSpot Free, Zoho CRM) by day 10, import existing customer data, define segments for active, lapsed and target prospects, and launch an email re-engagement campaign by day 25.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 22:48:32','2025-08-26 22:48:32'),(423,17,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Draft a sales and marketing strategy','Allocate 2 hours to workshop a 3-page plan: define target segments, key value propositions, communication channels and monthly lead targets. Present the draft to the team in week 3 for feedback and finalize by day 30.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 22:48:32','2025-08-26 22:48:32'),(424,17,NULL,NULL,0,'competitive-forces','Review and renegotiate key supplier contracts','List top 5 suppliers by spend, request current contract terms, and prepare negotiation points (pricing, payment terms, volume discounts). Schedule calls and aim to secure improved terms for at least two suppliers within 30 days.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 22:48:32','2025-08-26 22:48:32'),(425,17,NULL,NULL,0,'due-diligence','Estimate and plan property upgrade needs','Inspect the leased office at 8 Gregsue Ct, document required maintenance (e.g., painting, fixtures), obtain at least two quotes from contractors, and schedule works to be completed within the next 60 days to maintain compliance and appearance.',NULL,0,'low',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 22:48:32','2025-08-26 22:48:32'),(426,17,NULL,NULL,0,'diagnostic','Gather key working-capital metrics','Prepare a diagnostics checklist listing debtors, creditors, stock levels, WIP and forward orders. Assign each data point to a team member and collect actual figures by day 20 to feed into cash-flow modelling.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 22:48:32','2025-08-26 22:48:32'),(427,17,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Set up basic HR metrics and performance review schedule','Define 3 core HR metrics (utilisation rate, absenteeism, turnover). Create a tracker in a shared spreadsheet. Schedule one-on-one performance check-ins monthly instead of biannually, starting within the next 30 days.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 22:48:32','2025-08-26 22:48:32'),(428,17,NULL,NULL,0,'tax','Lodge Overdue BAS Statements','1. Gather all transaction records for the past periods. 2. Reconcile bank statements against sales and expenses. 3. Complete BAS forms for the outstanding quarters. 4. Engage your accountant (Bob Hope at Forsyths) to review and sign off. 5. Submit electronically via the ATO portal within 7 days and confirm receipt.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 23:04:38','2025-08-26 23:04:38'),(429,17,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Engage a Professional Bookkeeper','1. Draft a scope of work covering bank reconciliations, BAS preparation, WIP and debtor tracking. 2. Obtain quotes from at least three bookkeepers. 3. Check references and relevant industry experience. 4. Execute engagement letter and onboard via a kickoff meeting. 5. Provide access to financial systems and logins.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 23:04:38','2025-08-26 23:04:38'),(430,17,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Create a Weekly Working Capital Dashboard','1. Define key metrics: WIP value, debtors aging, creditors aging, stock levels. 2. Design an Excel or Google Sheet template. 3. Automate data imports or set up a weekly data-pull schedule. 4. Train bookkeeper to update each Monday. 5. Review the dashboard in Friday finance check-ins.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 23:04:38','2025-08-26 23:04:38'),(431,17,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Schedule Weekly Finance Review Meetings','1. Invite Stacey, your bookkeeper, and Bob Hope to a recurring 60-minute weekly slot. 2. Circulate an agenda covering cash flow, overdue debtors, and AP commitments. 3. Document actions and assign follow-ups. 4. Record minutes and share with all attendees within 24 hours.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 23:04:38','2025-08-26 23:04:38'),(432,17,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Document Core Business Processes','1. List all critical workflows (sales order, inventory receipt, production scheduling, finance close). 2. Use a process-mapping tool (e.g., Lucidchart or Visio). 3. Interview Stacey and key staff to capture steps, inputs, outputs and owners. 4. Review and validate with staff. 5. Store finalized SOPs in a shared folder with version control.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 23:04:38','2025-08-26 23:04:38'),(433,17,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Implement Basic Automation for Reporting','1. Identify reporting needs (P&L, cash flow, inventory). 2. Evaluate low-cost tools (Google Data Studio, Excel macros). 3. Set up data connectors to your accounting system or spreadsheets. 4. Create sample dashboards. 5. Train one staff member to update and maintain.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 23:04:38','2025-08-26 23:04:38'),(434,17,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Develop E-commerce Pilot and Digital Sales Strategy','1. Determine top 5 products for online sale. 2. Choose a basic platform (Shopify, WooCommerce). 3. Configure payment gateway and shipping options. 4. Upload product listings with descriptions and images. 5. Soft-launch with existing customer mailing list and monitor sales.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 23:04:38','2025-08-26 23:04:38'),(435,17,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Set Up CRM and Customer Segmentation','1. Evaluate simple CRM options (HubSpot free tier, Zoho CRM). 2. Import customer data from past 12 months. 3. Create segments: active, lapsed, lost. 4. Define fields for contact info, purchase history and next action. 5. Train staff on data entry and follow-up protocols.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 23:04:38','2025-08-26 23:04:38'),(436,17,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Launch Lost-Customer Win-Back Campaign','1. Extract list of customers with no purchases in past 6 months. 2. Draft a personalized email offer or discount. 3. Schedule outreach in batches of 20 per day. 4. Track responses and conversions in your new CRM. 5. Follow up by phone with top 10% unresponsive high-value customers.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 23:04:38','2025-08-26 23:04:38'),(437,17,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Engage External Legal Counsel and Review Current Actions','1. Identify a specialist in regulatory and commercial disputes. 2. Provide all legal action documents and correspondence. 3. Schedule a detailed review meeting within 7 days. 4. Obtain a risk and exposure report. 5. Agree on a mitigation plan and assign responsibilities.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 23:04:38','2025-08-26 23:04:38'),(438,17,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Draft Regulatory-Compliance Framework','1. List all applicable industry regulations and standards. 2. Gap-analyze existing practices against requirements. 3. Develop a compliance checklist and schedule for regular audits. 4. Assign ownership for each compliance area. 5. Integrate into monthly management review.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 23:04:38','2025-08-26 23:04:38'),(439,17,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Create a Succession and Delegation Plan','1. Document all key tasks currently performed by Stacey. 2. Identify internal candidates for each responsibility. 3. Develop hand-over timelines and training materials. 4. Schedule shadowing sessions over the next 4 weeks. 5. Finalize the plan and store in the governance folder.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 23:04:38','2025-08-26 23:04:38'),(440,17,NULL,NULL,0,'general','Formalize Weekly Internal Management Meetings','1. Set up a recurring 90-minute meeting with department leads. 2. Create a standard agenda: KPIs, risks, action items. 3. Assign a rotating meeting chair and note-taker. 4. Share minutes and hold each lead accountable for updates. 5. Review and adjust cadence after one month.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 23:04:38','2025-08-26 23:04:38'),(441,17,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Conduct Full Inventory and WIP Audit','1. Schedule a physical count of all stock and WIP items. 2. Reconcile counts against system records. 3. Identify obsolete or overstocked items. 4. Set minimum/maximum reorder thresholds. 5. Update inventory controls and train staff on cycle counts.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 23:04:38','2025-08-26 23:04:38'),(442,17,NULL,NULL,0,'competitive-forces','Negotiate Supplier Volume Discounts and Exclusivity','1. List top 5 suppliers by spend. 2. Request meetings or calls to discuss pricing and terms. 3. Propose volume tiers or exclusivity agreements in exchange for lower unit costs. 4. Evaluate counter-offers and finalize contract amendments. 5. Document new terms and communicate to purchasing team.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 23:04:38','2025-08-26 23:04:38'),(443,17,NULL,NULL,0,'due-diligence','Assemble Due Diligence Data Room','1. Collect P&L statements for the past 3–5 years. 2. Prepare forward-orders list, debt schedules, leases, encumbrances and IP details. 3. Organize documents in a secure shared folder with clear folder structure. 4. Add track-changes and version control. 5. Grant view-only access to advisors and potential buyers.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-26 23:04:38','2025-08-26 23:04:38'),(444,15,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Separate Migration and Education Divisions','1. Convene a 2-hour strategy meeting with Shannon and senior managers. 2. Map existing workflows, revenue streams and cost centers for both Migration and Education. 3. Create two P&L templates in Xero or your accounting system. 4. Assign divisional heads and update the organisational chart. 5. Communicate the new structure internally and update all process documentation.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:06:49','2025-09-02 00:06:49'),(445,15,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Conduct Divisional Financial Segmentation','1. Work with Brad Thom at Thomas and Noble to extract last 12 months\' revenue and cost data by division. 2. Tag each transaction in Xero by division. 3. Generate separate P&L and balance sheet reports. 4. Review variances and adjust intercompany allocations. 5. Save segmented financials for buyer presentations.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:06:49','2025-09-02 00:06:49'),(446,15,NULL,NULL,0,'due-diligence','Evaluate CRM Solutions','1. List must-have features (pipeline visibility, automated nurturing, reporting to 7/10 standard). 2. Gather quotes from Go High Level, HubSpot and two other vendors. 3. Book product demos and score each on functionality, ease of migration and cost. 4. Prepare a comparison matrix. 5. Present recommendation at next weekly executive meeting.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:06:49','2025-09-02 00:06:49'),(447,15,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Plan and Execute CRM Upgrade','1. Once vendor selected, assign a project lead. 2. Export Salesforce data and perform a data cleanse. 3. Build out Go High Level instance with custom fields and pipelines. 4. Migrate 3 months of test data and validate accuracy. 5. Train sales and marketing teams with two 1-hour workshops. 6. Switch off Salesforce and set go-live date.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:06:49','2025-09-02 00:06:49'),(448,15,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Eliminate WIP Backlog','1. Audit all active jobs older than 3 days; document status and blockers. 2. Reallocate resources or hire freelancers to clear the 50K backlog. 3. Implement a daily stand-up for job status and target completions. 4. Set KPI dashboard tracking turnaround time and escalate any over-3-day items. 5. Report progress to Shannon every Friday.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:06:49','2025-09-02 00:06:49'),(449,15,NULL,NULL,0,'general','Develop Post-Sale Continuity Plan','1. Identify critical founder activities and map required skills. 2. Select at least two deputies from current management. 3. Organise shadowing sessions and assign key tasks. 4. Draft a 30-page continuity manual covering decision-making protocols. 5. Review plan with external M&A advisor to ensure buyer confidence.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:06:49','2025-09-02 00:06:49'),(450,15,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Document Operational Manuals for Migration Division','1. Gather existing SOPs and process docs. 2. Conduct 1:1 interviews with process owners to capture tacit knowledge. 3. Update and standardise templates in Google Drive. 4. Link each SOP to a training video or slide deck. 5. Distribute drafts for peer review and final sign-off by Shannon.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:06:49','2025-09-02 00:06:49'),(451,15,NULL,NULL,0,'due-diligence','Compile and Validate Financial Due Diligence Pack','1. Collect final P&L, balance sheets and tax returns from the last 5 years. 2. Verify all were prepared by a Chartered Accountant. 3. Ensure management accounts are up to date. 4. Incorporate variance analyses and forecasts. 5. Organise all documents in a virtual data room with clear folder structure.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:06:49','2025-09-02 00:06:49'),(452,15,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Prepare Transparent Debt Schedule for Buyers','1. List each debt: original amount, remaining term, interest rate, repayment schedule. 2. Obtain lender statements and repayment history. 3. Create a 1-page debt summary and a detailed amortisation table. 4. Highlight any pre-payment or transfer conditions. 5. Include both in the buyer data room.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:06:49','2025-09-02 00:06:49'),(453,15,NULL,NULL,0,'customers','Implement Marketing Analytics Dashboard','1. Audit current online spend and tracking tools (Google Analytics, ad platforms). 2. Define key metrics (CPL, ROI, CAC). 3. Set up a dashboard in Google Data Studio or Power BI. 4. Integrate spend data from Facebook, Google Ads and LinkedIn. 5. Train the marketing team to update weekly and review monthly.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:06:49','2025-09-02 00:06:49'),(454,15,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Migrate Salesforce Data to Go High Level','1. Export all contacts, leads, opportunities and activities from Salesforce. 2. Cleanse duplicates and outdated records. 3. Map Salesforce fields to Go High Level equivalents. 4. Import data in batches and validate record counts. 5. Run reconciliation reports to confirm 100% data accuracy.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:06:49','2025-09-02 00:06:49'),(455,15,NULL,NULL,0,'competitive-forces','Pilot AI Voice Agent in Education Division','1. Identify 2-3 customer touchpoints for the AI Voice Agent. 2. Develop a pilot script and integrate with Eleven Labs or OpenAI API. 3. Train the AI with 50 sample calls. 4. Run a 1-week live pilot with a small customer cohort. 5. Measure time savings, customer feedback and error rates.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:06:49','2025-09-02 00:06:49'),(456,15,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Conduct Retention and Succession Workshops','1. Schedule two 2-hour workshops: one on retention strategies for at-risk staff, one on succession coverage. 2. Use pulse surveys to identify why key employees might leave. 3. Draft retention plans including career paths and incentives. 4. Assign mentors and cross-training buddies. 5. Review progress in 30 days.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:06:49','2025-09-02 00:06:49'),(457,15,NULL,NULL,0,'competitive-forces','Perform Competitive Landscape Update','1. Re-audit four main competitors: product/service offerings, pricing and market positioning. 2. Assess new threats from AI and policy changes. 3. Update SWOT grid and barrier-to-entry analysis. 4. Highlight where our NPS and AI tools provide an edge. 5. Circulate findings to sales, marketing and strategy teams.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:06:49','2025-09-02 00:06:49'),(458,15,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Review Migration Agent Code of Conduct Compliance','1. Obtain the latest Migration Agent Code of Conduct. 2. Cross-check all migration processes against each clause. 3. Document any gaps and assign responsible owners. 4. Develop an action plan to close compliance gaps within 14 days. 5. Sign off by legal counsel and retain evidence for buyer review.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:06:49','2025-09-02 00:06:49'),(459,15,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Separate Migration and Education Divisions','1. Map existing processes and revenue streams for each division. 2. Create separate profit and loss tracking codes in Xero for migration and education. 3. Assign division leads and update the org chart. 4. Schedule separate weekly management meetings for each division. 5. Communicate the new structure to staff and update internal documentation.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:07:00','2025-09-02 00:07:00'),(460,15,NULL,NULL,0,'legal-licensing','Establish Division-Specific Legal and Financial Structures','1. Consult with your accountant (Brad Thom) and legal advisor on whether to form separate subsidiaries or trade names. 2. Prepare and file any required entity formation documents. 3. Open dedicated bank accounts for each division. 4. Update shareholder agreements and internal policies to reflect the new structure. 5. Notify stakeholders and suppliers of the new banking details.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:07:00','2025-09-02 00:07:00'),(461,15,NULL,NULL,0,'due-diligence','Prepare a Divisional Due Diligence Data Room','1. Create a secure cloud folder structure labelled ‘Migration Division’ and ‘Education Division’. 2. Upload the last 3 years of P&L, balance sheets, debt schedules, and key contracts by division. 3. Include a schedule of the $70K outstanding debt and repayment status. 4. Add operational manuals, IP documentation, and AI project summaries. 5. Set user permissions and share access details with the M&A advisor.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:07:00','2025-09-02 00:07:00'),(462,15,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Upgrade and Migrate to Go High Level CRM','1. Document current CRM requirements and pain points. 2. Backup all Salesforce data. 3. Configure Go High Level sandbox environment. 4. Map and import contacts, deals, and marketing automations. 5. Build lead nurturing sequences, test workflows, and train the sales team. 6. Decommission legacy Salesforce access once Go High Level is live.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:07:00','2025-09-02 00:07:00'),(463,15,NULL,NULL,0,'operations','Eliminate Three-Day WIP Bottleneck','1. Map the end-to-end client engagement process to spot delays. 2. Hold a cross-functional workshop to identify root causes. 3. Reallocate or hire temporary resource to clear the current $50K WIP. 4. Introduce a daily WIP dashboard and 15-minute morning huddle. 5. Set a target of clearing all new work within two business days.',NULL,0,'critical',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:07:00','2025-09-02 00:07:00'),(464,15,NULL,NULL,0,'human-resources','Strengthen Succession and Continuity Plans','1. Review existing succession documents and identify gaps. 2. Appoint an internal deputy for the migration division. 3. Document detailed step-by-step workflows for the owner’s role. 4. Conduct two shadowing and training sessions. 5. Finalize and distribute operational manuals. 6. Verify that the business can run for one week without founder input.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:07:00','2025-09-02 00:07:00'),(465,15,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Implement Marketing Analytics Dashboard','1. List all sales and marketing spend channels. 2. Define KPIs (CPL, CAC, ROI, conversion rates). 3. Build a Google Data Studio dashboard integrating Google Analytics, social media, and CRM data. 4. Automate weekly refresh and distribute to marketing and senior leadership. 5. Train the marketing team to interpret and act on insights.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:07:00','2025-09-02 00:07:00'),(466,15,NULL,NULL,0,'financial','Package Education Arm as a Standalone Asset','1. Compile a schedule of the £1.4M pre-committed contracts and associated costs. 2. Build a financial model showing revenue, cost base (<£60K), and margin. 3. Draft an executive summary highlighting locked-in income and growth potential. 4. Design a one-page investment teaser. 5. Coordinate with M&A advisor to distribute to target buyers.',NULL,0,'high',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:07:00','2025-09-02 00:07:00'),(467,15,NULL,NULL,0,'competitive-forces','Deploy and Document AI Voice Agent and Assessment Tools','1. Complete pilot deployment with 5 existing clients. 2. Capture performance metrics (call handle time, accuracy, cost savings). 3. Document installation and configuration steps in a technical manual. 4. Prepare a case study quantifying margin uplift. 5. Package this documentation for buyer marketing materials.',NULL,0,'medium',0,'needs-action',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-02 00:07:00','2025-09-02 00:07:00'),(468,15,NULL,NULL,0,'tax','Engage a Bookkeeper for Ongoing Financial Management','1. Draft a role description for a part-time bookkeeper. 2. Post the position